  19.            (* Tools to manipulate scanning set of chars (see %[...]) *)

  21. ‌type mutable_char_set = bytes

  23. (* Create a fresh, empty, mutable char set. *)
  24. ‌let create_char_set () = Bytes.make 32 '\000'

  26. (* Add a char in a mutable char set. *)
  27. ‌let add_in_char_set char_set c =
  28.   let ind = int_of_char c in
  29.   let str_ind = ind lsr 3 and mask = 1 lsl (ind land 0b111) in
  30.   Bytes.set char_set str_ind
  31.     (char_of_int (int_of_char (Bytes.get char_set str_ind) lor mask))

  33. ‌let freeze_char_set char_set =
  34.   Bytes.to_string char_set

  36. (* Compute the complement of a char set. *)
  37. ‌let rev_char_set char_set =
  38.   let char_set' = create_char_set () in
  39.   for i = 0 to 31 do
  40.     Bytes.set char_set' i
  41.       (char_of_int (int_of_char (String.get char_set i) lxor 0xFF));
  42.   done;
  43.   Bytes.unsafe_to_string char_set'

  45. (* Return true if a `c' is in `char_set'. *)
  46. ‌let is_in_char_set char_set c =
  47.   let ind = int_of_char c in
  48.   let str_ind = ind lsr 3 and mask = 1 lsl (ind land 0b111) in
  49.   (int_of_char (String.get char_set str_ind) land mask) <> 0

  53.                          (* Ignored param conversion *)

  55. (* GADT used to abstract an existential type parameter. *)
  56. (* See param_format_of_ignored_format. *)
  57. ‌type ('a, 'b, 'c, 'd, 'e, 'f) param_format_ebb = Param_format_EBB :
  58.     ('x -> 'a, 'b, 'c, 'd, 'e, 'f) fmt ->
  59.     ('a, 'b, 'c, 'd, 'e, 'f) param_format_ebb

  61. (* Compute a padding associated to a pad_option (see "%_42d"). *)
  62. ‌let pad_of_pad_opt pad_opt = match pad_opt with
  63.   | None -> No_padding
  64.   | Some width -> Lit_padding (Right, width)

  66. (* Compute a precision associated to a prec_option (see "%_.42f"). *)
  67. ‌let prec_of_prec_opt prec_opt = match prec_opt with
  68.   | None -> No_precision
  69.   | Some ndec -> Lit_precision ndec

  71. (* Turn an ignored param into its equivalent not-ignored format node. *)
  72. (* Used for format pretty-printing and Scanf. *)
  73. ‌‌let param_format_of_ignored_format : type a b c d e f x y .
  74.     (a, b, c, d, y, x) ignored -> (x, b, c, y, e, f) fmt ->
  75.       (a, b, c, d, e, f) param_format_ebb =
  76. fun ign fmt -> match ign with
  77.   | Ignored_char ->
  78.     Param_format_EBB (Char fmt)
  79.   | Ignored_caml_char ->
  80.     Param_format_EBB (Caml_char fmt)
  81.   | Ignored_string pad_opt ->
  82.     Param_format_EBB (String (pad_of_pad_opt pad_opt, fmt))
  83.   | Ignored_caml_string pad_opt ->
  84.     Param_format_EBB (Caml_string (pad_of_pad_opt pad_opt, fmt))
  85.   | Ignored_int (iconv, pad_opt) ->
  86.     Param_format_EBB (Int (iconv, pad_of_pad_opt pad_opt, No_precision, fmt))
  87.   | Ignored_int32 (iconv, pad_opt) ->
  88.     Param_format_EBB
  89.       (Int32 (iconv, pad_of_pad_opt pad_opt, No_precision, fmt))
  90.   | Ignored_nativeint (iconv, pad_opt) ->
  91.     Param_format_EBB
  92.       (Nativeint (iconv, pad_of_pad_opt pad_opt, No_precision, fmt))
  93.   | Ignored_int64 (iconv, pad_opt) ->
  94.     Param_format_EBB
  95.       (Int64 (iconv, pad_of_pad_opt pad_opt, No_precision, fmt))
  96.   | Ignored_float (pad_opt, prec_opt) ->
  97.     Param_format_EBB
  98.       (Float ((Float_flag_, Float_f),
  99.               pad_of_pad_opt pad_opt, prec_of_prec_opt prec_opt, fmt))
  100.   | Ignored_bool pad_opt ->
  101.     Param_format_EBB (Bool (pad_of_pad_opt pad_opt, fmt))
  102.   | Ignored_format_arg (pad_opt, fmtty) ->
  103.     Param_format_EBB (Format_arg (pad_opt, fmtty, fmt))
  104.   | Ignored_format_subst (pad_opt, fmtty) ->
  105.     Param_format_EBB
  106.       (Format_subst (pad_opt, fmtty, fmt))
  107.   | Ignored_reader ->
  108.     Param_format_EBB (Reader fmt)
  109.   | Ignored_scan_char_set (width_opt, char_set) ->
  110.     Param_format_EBB (Scan_char_set (width_opt, char_set, fmt))
  111.   | Ignored_scan_get_counter counter ->
  112.     Param_format_EBB (Scan_get_counter (counter, fmt))
  113.   | Ignored_scan_next_char ->
  114.     Param_format_EBB (Scan_next_char fmt)

  217.                                (* Constants *)

  219. (* Default precision for float printing. *)
  220. ‌let default_float_precision fconv =
  221.   match snd fconv with
  222.   | Float_f | Float_e | Float_E | Float_g | Float_G | Float_h | Float_H
  223.   | Float_CF -> -6
  224.   (* For %h %H and %#F formats, a negative precision means "as many digits as
  225.      necessary".  For the other FP formats, we take the absolute value
  226.      of the precision, hence 6 digits by default. *)
  227.   | Float_F -> 12
  228.   (* Default precision for OCaml float printing (%F). *)

  239. external format_nativeint: string -> nativeint -> string
  240.   = "caml_nativeint_format"
  241. external format_int64: string -> int64 -> string
  242.   = "caml_int64_format"
  243. external hexstring_of_float: float -> int -> char -> string
  244.   = "caml_hexstring_of_float"

  246. (******************************************************************************)
  247.                      (* Tools to pretty-print formats *)

  249. (* Type of extensible character buffers. *)
  250. ‌type buffer = {
  251.   mutable ind : int;
  252.   mutable bytes : bytes;
  253. }

  255. (* Create a fresh buffer. *)
  256. ‌let buffer_create init_size = { ind = 0; bytes = Bytes.create init_size }

  258. (* Check size of the buffer and grow it if needed. *)
  259. ‌let buffer_check_size buf overhead =
  260.   let len = Bytes.length buf.bytes in
  261.   let min_len = buf.ind + overhead in
  262.   if min_len > len then (
  263.     let new_len = Int.max (len * 2) min_len in
  264.     let new_str = Bytes.create new_len in
  265.     Bytes.blit buf.bytes 0 new_str 0 len;
  266.     buf.bytes <- new_str;
  267.   )

  269. (* Add the character `c' to the buffer `buf'. *)
  270. ‌let buffer_add_char buf c =
  271.   buffer_check_size buf 1;
  272.   Bytes.set buf.bytes buf.ind c;
  273.   buf.ind <- buf.ind + 1

  275. (* Add the string `s' to the buffer `buf'. *)
  276. ‌let buffer_add_string buf s =
  277.   let str_len = String.length s in
  278.   buffer_check_size buf str_len;
  279.   String.blit s 0 buf.bytes buf.ind str_len;
  280.   buf.ind <- buf.ind + str_len

  282. (* Get the content of the buffer. *)
  283. ‌let buffer_contents buf =
  284.   Bytes.sub_string buf.bytes 0 buf.ind

  286. (***)

  288. (* Convert an integer conversion to char. *)
  289. ‌let char_of_iconv iconv = match iconv with
  290.   | Int_d | Int_pd | Int_sd | Int_Cd -> 'd' | Int_i | Int_pi | Int_si
  291.   | Int_Ci -> 'i' | Int_x | Int_Cx -> 'x' | Int_X | Int_CX -> 'X' | Int_o
  292.   | Int_Co -> 'o' | Int_u | Int_Cu -> 'u'

  294. (* Convert a float conversion to char. *)
  295. (* `cF' will be 'F' for displaying format and 'g' to call libc printf *)
  296. ‌let char_of_fconv ?(cF='F') fconv = match snd fconv with
  297.   | Float_f -> 'f' | Float_e -> 'e'
  298.   | Float_E -> 'E' | Float_g -> 'g'
  299.   | Float_G -> 'G' | Float_F -> cF
  300.   | Float_h -> 'h' | Float_H -> 'H'
  301.   | Float_CF -> 'F'


  304. (* Convert a scanning counter to char. *)
  305. ‌let char_of_counter counter = match counter with
  306.   | Line_counter  -> 'l'
  307.   | Char_counter  -> 'n'
  308.   | Token_counter -> 'N'

  310. (***)

  312. (* Print a char_set in a buffer with the OCaml format lexical convention. *)
  313. ‌let bprint_char_set buf char_set =
  314.   let rec print_start set =
  315.     let is_alone c =
  316.       let before, after = Char.(chr (code c - 1), chr (code c + 1)) in
  317.       is_in_char_set set c
  318.       && not (is_in_char_set set before && is_in_char_set set after) in
  319.     if is_alone ']' then buffer_add_char buf ']';
  320.     print_out set 1;
  321.     if is_alone '-' then buffer_add_char buf '-';
  322.   and print_out set i =
  323.     if i < 256 then
  324.       if is_in_char_set set (char_of_int i) then print_first set i
  325.       else print_out set (i + 1)
  326.   and print_first set i =
  327.     match char_of_int i with
  328.     | '\255' -> print_char buf 255;
  329.     | ']' | '-' -> print_out set (i + 1);
  330.     | _ -> print_second set (i + 1);
  331.   and print_second set i =
  332.     if is_in_char_set set (char_of_int i) then
  333.       match char_of_int i with
  334.       | '\255' ->
  335.         print_char buf 254;
  336.         print_char buf 255;
  337.       | ']' | '-' when not (is_in_char_set set (char_of_int (i + 1))) ->
  338.         print_char buf (i - 1);
  339.         print_out set (i + 1);
  340.       | _ when not (is_in_char_set set (char_of_int (i + 1))) ->
  341.         print_char buf (i - 1);
  342.         print_char buf i;
  343.         print_out set (i + 2);
  344.       | _ ->
  345.         print_in set (i - 1) (i + 2);
  346.     else (
  347.       print_char buf (i - 1);
  348.       print_out set (i + 1);
  349.     )
  350.   and print_in set i j =
  351.     if j = 256 || not (is_in_char_set set (char_of_int j)) then (
  352.       print_char buf i;
  353.       print_char buf (int_of_char '-');
  354.       print_char buf (j - 1);
  355.       if j < 256 then print_out set (j + 1);
  356.     ) else
  357.       print_in set i (j + 1);
  358.   and print_char buf i = match char_of_int i with
  359.     | '%' -> buffer_add_char buf '%'; buffer_add_char buf '%';
  360.     | '@' -> buffer_add_char buf '%'; buffer_add_char buf '@';
  361.     | c   -> buffer_add_char buf c;
  362.   in
  363.   buffer_add_char buf '[';
  364.   print_start (
  365.     if is_in_char_set char_set '\000'
  366.     then ( buffer_add_char buf '^'; rev_char_set char_set )
  367.     else char_set
  368.   );
  369.   buffer_add_char buf ']'

  371. (***)

  373. (* Print a padty in a buffer with the format-like syntax. *)
  374. ‌let bprint_padty buf padty = match padty with
  375.   | Left  -> buffer_add_char buf '-'
  376.   | Right -> ()
  377.   | Zeros -> buffer_add_char buf '0'

  379. (* Print the '_' of an ignored flag if needed. *)
  380. ‌let bprint_ignored_flag buf ign_flag =
  381.   if ign_flag then buffer_add_char buf '_'

  383. (***)

  385. ‌let bprint_pad_opt buf pad_opt = match pad_opt with
  386.   | None -> ()
  387.   | Some width -> buffer_add_string buf (Int.to_string width)

  389. (***)

  391. (* Print padding in a buffer with the format-like syntax. *)
  392. ‌‌let bprint_padding : type a b . buffer -> (a, b) padding -> unit =
  393. fun buf pad -> match pad with
  394.   | No_padding -> ()
  395.   | Lit_padding (padty, n) ->
  396.     bprint_padty buf padty;
  397.     buffer_add_string buf (Int.to_string n);
  398.   | Arg_padding padty ->
  399.     bprint_padty buf padty;
  400.     buffer_add_char buf '*'

  402. (* Print precision in a buffer with the format-like syntax. *)
  403. ‌‌let bprint_precision : type a b . buffer -> (a, b) precision -> unit =
  404.   fun buf prec -> match prec with
  405.   | No_precision -> ()
  406.   | Lit_precision n ->
  407.     buffer_add_char buf '.';
  408.     buffer_add_string buf (Int.to_string n);
  409.   | Arg_precision ->
  410.     buffer_add_string buf ".*"

  412. (***)

  414. (* Print the optional '+', ' ' or '#' associated to an int conversion. *)
  415. ‌let bprint_iconv_flag buf iconv = match iconv with
  416.   | Int_pd | Int_pi -> buffer_add_char buf '+'
  417.   | Int_sd | Int_si -> buffer_add_char buf ' '
  418.   | Int_Cx | Int_CX | Int_Co | Int_Cd | Int_Ci | Int_Cu ->
  419.       buffer_add_char buf '#'
  420.   | Int_d | Int_i | Int_x | Int_X | Int_o | Int_u -> ()

  422. (* Print an complete int format in a buffer (ex: "%3.*d"). *)
  423. ‌let bprint_int_fmt buf ign_flag iconv pad prec =
  424.   buffer_add_char buf '%';
  425.   bprint_ignored_flag buf ign_flag;
  426.   bprint_iconv_flag buf iconv;
  427.   bprint_padding buf pad;
  428.   bprint_precision buf prec;
  429.   buffer_add_char buf (char_of_iconv iconv)

  431. (* Print a complete int32, nativeint or int64 format in a buffer. *)
  432. ‌let bprint_altint_fmt buf ign_flag iconv pad prec c =
  433.   buffer_add_char buf '%';
  434.   bprint_ignored_flag buf ign_flag;
  435.   bprint_iconv_flag buf iconv;
  436.   bprint_padding buf pad;
  437.   bprint_precision buf prec;
  438.   buffer_add_char buf c;
  439.   buffer_add_char buf (char_of_iconv iconv)

  441. (***)

  443. (* Print the optional '+', ' ' and/or '#' associated to a float conversion. *)
  444. ‌let bprint_fconv_flag buf fconv =
  445.   begin match fst fconv with
  446.   | Float_flag_p -> buffer_add_char buf '+'
  447.   | Float_flag_s -> buffer_add_char buf ' '
  448.   | Float_flag_ -> () end;
  449.   match snd fconv with
  450.   | Float_CF -> buffer_add_char buf '#'
  451.   | Float_f | Float_e | Float_E | Float_g | Float_G
  452.   | Float_F | Float_h | Float_H -> ()

  454. (* Print a complete float format in a buffer (ex: "%+*.3f"). *)
  455. ‌let bprint_float_fmt buf ign_flag fconv pad prec =
  456.   buffer_add_char buf '%';
  457.   bprint_ignored_flag buf ign_flag;
  458.   bprint_fconv_flag buf fconv;
  459.   bprint_padding buf pad;
  460.   bprint_precision buf prec;
  461.   buffer_add_char buf (char_of_fconv fconv)

  463. (* Compute the literal string representation of a Formatting_lit. *)
  464. (* Used by Printf and Scanf where formatting is not interpreted. *)
  465. ‌let string_of_formatting_lit formatting_lit = match formatting_lit with
  466.   | Close_box            -> "@]"
  467.   | Close_tag            -> "@}"
  468.   | Break (str, _, _)    -> str
  469.   | FFlush               -> "@?"
  470.   | Force_newline        -> "@\n"
  471.   | Flush_newline        -> "@."
  472.   | Magic_size (str, _)  -> str
  473.   | Escaped_at           -> "@@"
  474.   | Escaped_percent      -> "@%"
  475.   | Scan_indic c -> "@" ^ (String.make 1 c)

  477. (***)

  479. (* Print a literal char in a buffer, escape '%' by "%%". *)
  480. ‌let bprint_char_literal buf chr = match chr with
  481.   | '%' -> buffer_add_string buf "%%"
  482.   | _ -> buffer_add_char buf chr

  484. (* Print a literal string in a buffer, escape all '%' by "%%". *)
  485. ‌let bprint_string_literal buf str =
  486.   for i = 0 to String.length str - 1 do
  487.     bprint_char_literal buf str.[i]
  488.   done

  490. (******************************************************************************)
  491.                           (* Format pretty-printing *)

  493. (* Print a complete format type (an fmtty) in a buffer. *)
  494. ‌‌let rec bprint_fmtty : type a b c d e f g h i j k l .
  495.     buffer -> (a, b, c, d, e, f, g, h, i, j, k, l) fmtty_rel -> unit =
  496. fun buf fmtty -> match fmtty with
  497.   | Char_ty rest      -> buffer_add_string buf "%c";  bprint_fmtty buf rest;
  498.   | String_ty rest    -> buffer_add_string buf "%s";  bprint_fmtty buf rest;
  499.   | Int_ty rest       -> buffer_add_string buf "%i";  bprint_fmtty buf rest;
  500.   | Int32_ty rest     -> buffer_add_string buf "%li"; bprint_fmtty buf rest;
  501.   | Nativeint_ty rest -> buffer_add_string buf "%ni"; bprint_fmtty buf rest;
  502.   | Int64_ty rest     -> buffer_add_string buf "%Li"; bprint_fmtty buf rest;
  503.   | Float_ty rest     -> buffer_add_string buf "%f";  bprint_fmtty buf rest;
  504.   | Bool_ty rest      -> buffer_add_string buf "%B";  bprint_fmtty buf rest;
  505.   | Alpha_ty rest     -> buffer_add_string buf "%a";  bprint_fmtty buf rest;
  506.   | Theta_ty rest     -> buffer_add_string buf "%t";  bprint_fmtty buf rest;
  507.   | Any_ty rest       -> buffer_add_string buf "%?";  bprint_fmtty buf rest;
  508.   | Reader_ty rest    -> buffer_add_string buf "%r";  bprint_fmtty buf rest;

  510.   | Ignored_reader_ty rest ->
  511.     buffer_add_string buf "%_r";
  512.     bprint_fmtty buf rest;

  514.   | Format_arg_ty (sub_fmtty, rest) ->
  515.     buffer_add_string buf "%{"; bprint_fmtty buf sub_fmtty;
  516.     buffer_add_string buf "%}"; bprint_fmtty buf rest;
  517.   | Format_subst_ty (sub_fmtty, _, rest) ->
  518.     buffer_add_string buf "%("; bprint_fmtty buf sub_fmtty;
  519.     buffer_add_string buf "%)"; bprint_fmtty buf rest;

  521.   | End_of_fmtty -> ()

  523. (***)

  525. ‌‌let rec int_of_custom_arity : type a b c .
  526.   (a, b, c) custom_arity -> int =
  527.   function
  528.   | Custom_zero -> 0
  529.   | Custom_succ x -> 1 + int_of_custom_arity x

  531. (* Print a complete format in a buffer. *)
  532. ‌let bprint_fmt buf fmt =
  533. ‌  let rec fmtiter : type a b c d e f .
  534.       (a, b, c, d, e, f) fmt -> bool -> unit =
  535.   fun fmt ign_flag -> match fmt with
  536.     | String (pad, rest) ->
  537.       buffer_add_char buf '%'; bprint_ignored_flag buf ign_flag;
  538.       bprint_padding buf pad; buffer_add_char buf 's';
  539.       fmtiter rest false;
  540.     | Caml_string (pad, rest) ->
  541.       buffer_add_char buf '%'; bprint_ignored_flag buf ign_flag;
  542.       bprint_padding buf pad; buffer_add_char buf 'S';
  543.       fmtiter rest false;

  545.     | Int (iconv, pad, prec, rest) ->
  546.       bprint_int_fmt buf ign_flag iconv pad prec;
  547.       fmtiter rest false;
  548.     | Int32 (iconv, pad, prec, rest) ->
  549.       bprint_altint_fmt buf ign_flag iconv pad prec 'l';
  550.       fmtiter rest false;
  551.     | Nativeint (iconv, pad, prec, rest) ->
  552.       bprint_altint_fmt buf ign_flag iconv pad prec 'n';
  553.       fmtiter rest false;
  554.     | Int64 (iconv, pad, prec, rest) ->
  555.       bprint_altint_fmt buf ign_flag iconv pad prec 'L';
  556.       fmtiter rest false;
  557.     | Float (fconv, pad, prec, rest) ->
  558.       bprint_float_fmt buf ign_flag fconv pad prec;
  559.       fmtiter rest false;

  561.     | Char rest ->
  562.       buffer_add_char buf '%'; bprint_ignored_flag buf ign_flag;
  563.       buffer_add_char buf 'c'; fmtiter rest false;
  564.     | Caml_char rest ->
  565.       buffer_add_char buf '%'; bprint_ignored_flag buf ign_flag;
  566.       buffer_add_char buf 'C'; fmtiter rest false;
  567.     | Bool (pad, rest) ->
  568.       buffer_add_char buf '%'; bprint_ignored_flag buf ign_flag;
  569.       bprint_padding buf pad; buffer_add_char buf 'B';
  570.       fmtiter rest false;
  571.     | Alpha rest ->
  572.       buffer_add_char buf '%'; bprint_ignored_flag buf ign_flag;
  573.       buffer_add_char buf 'a'; fmtiter rest false;
  574.     | Theta rest ->
  575.       buffer_add_char buf '%'; bprint_ignored_flag buf ign_flag;
  576.       buffer_add_char buf 't'; fmtiter rest false;
  577.     | Custom (arity, _, rest) ->
  578.       for _i = 1 to int_of_custom_arity arity do
  579.         buffer_add_char buf '%'; bprint_ignored_flag buf ign_flag;
  580.         buffer_add_char buf '?';
  581.       done;
  582.       fmtiter rest false;
  583.     | Reader rest ->
  584.       buffer_add_char buf '%'; bprint_ignored_flag buf ign_flag;
  585.       buffer_add_char buf 'r'; fmtiter rest false;
  586.     | Flush rest ->
  587.       buffer_add_string buf "%!";
  588.       fmtiter rest ign_flag;

  590.     | String_literal (str, rest) ->
  591.       bprint_string_literal buf str;
  592.       fmtiter rest ign_flag;
  593.     | Char_literal (chr, rest) ->
  594.       bprint_char_literal buf chr;
  595.       fmtiter rest ign_flag;

  597.     | Format_arg (pad_opt, fmtty, rest) ->
  598.       buffer_add_char buf '%'; bprint_ignored_flag buf ign_flag;
  599.       bprint_pad_opt buf pad_opt; buffer_add_char buf '{';
  600.       bprint_fmtty buf fmtty; buffer_add_char buf '%'; buffer_add_char buf '}';
  601.       fmtiter rest false;
  602.     | Format_subst (pad_opt, fmtty, rest) ->
  603.       buffer_add_char buf '%'; bprint_ignored_flag buf ign_flag;
  604.       bprint_pad_opt buf pad_opt; buffer_add_char buf '(';
  605.       bprint_fmtty buf fmtty; buffer_add_char buf '%'; buffer_add_char buf ')';
  606.       fmtiter rest false;

  608.     | Scan_char_set (width_opt, char_set, rest) ->
  609.       buffer_add_char buf '%'; bprint_ignored_flag buf ign_flag;
  610.       bprint_pad_opt buf width_opt; bprint_char_set buf char_set;
  611.       fmtiter rest false;
  612.     | Scan_get_counter (counter, rest) ->
  613.       buffer_add_char buf '%'; bprint_ignored_flag buf ign_flag;
  614.       buffer_add_char buf (char_of_counter counter);
  615.       fmtiter rest false;
  616.     | Scan_next_char rest ->
  617.       buffer_add_char buf '%'; bprint_ignored_flag buf ign_flag;
  618.       bprint_string_literal buf "0c"; fmtiter rest false;

  620.     | Ignored_param (ign, rest) ->
  621. ‌      let Param_format_EBB fmt' = param_format_of_ignored_format ign rest in
  622.       fmtiter fmt' true;

  624.     | Formatting_lit (fmting_lit, rest) ->
  625.       bprint_string_literal buf (string_of_formatting_lit fmting_lit);
  626.       fmtiter rest ign_flag;
  627.     | Formatting_gen (fmting_gen, rest) ->
  628.       begin match fmting_gen with
  629.       | Open_tag (Format (_, str)) ->
  630.         buffer_add_string buf "@{"; buffer_add_string buf str
  631.       | Open_box (Format (_, str)) ->
  632.         buffer_add_string buf "@["; buffer_add_string buf str
  633.       end;
  634.       fmtiter rest ign_flag;

  636.     | End_of_format -> ()

  638.   in fmtiter fmt false

  640. (***)

  642. (* Convert a format to string. *)
  643. ‌let string_of_fmt fmt =
  644.   let buf = buffer_create 16 in
  645.   bprint_fmt buf fmt;
  646.   buffer_contents buf

  648. (******************************************************************************)
  649.                           (* Type extraction *)

  651. ‌type (_, _) eq = Refl : ('a, 'a) eq

  653. (* Invariant: this function is the identity on values.

  655.    In particular, if (ty1, ty2) have equal values, then
  656.    (trans (symm ty1) ty2) respects the 'trans' precondition. *)
  657. ‌‌let rec symm : type a1 b1 c1 d1 e1 f1 a2 b2 c2 d2 e2 f2 .
  658.    (a1, b1, c1, d1, e1, f1,
  659.     a2, b2, c2, d2, e2, f2) fmtty_rel
  660. -> (a2, b2, c2, d2, e2, f2,
  661.     a1, b1, c1, d1, e1, f1) fmtty_rel
  662. = function
  663.   | Char_ty rest -> Char_ty (symm rest)
  664.   | Int_ty rest -> Int_ty (symm rest)
  665.   | Int32_ty rest -> Int32_ty (symm rest)
  666.   | Int64_ty rest -> Int64_ty (symm rest)
  667.   | Nativeint_ty rest -> Nativeint_ty (symm rest)
  668.   | Float_ty rest -> Float_ty (symm rest)
  669.   | Bool_ty rest -> Bool_ty (symm rest)
  670.   | String_ty rest -> String_ty (symm rest)
  671.   | Theta_ty rest -> Theta_ty (symm rest)
  672.   | Alpha_ty rest -> Alpha_ty (symm rest)
  673.   | Any_ty rest -> Any_ty (symm rest)
  674.   | Reader_ty rest -> Reader_ty (symm rest)
  675.   | Ignored_reader_ty rest -> Ignored_reader_ty (symm rest)
  676.   | Format_arg_ty (ty, rest) ->
  677.     Format_arg_ty (ty, symm rest)
  678.   | Format_subst_ty (ty1, ty2, rest) ->
  679.     Format_subst_ty (ty2, ty1, symm rest)
  680.   | End_of_fmtty -> End_of_fmtty

  682. ‌‌let rec fmtty_rel_det : type a1 b c d1 e1 f1 a2 d2 e2 f2 .
  683.   (a1, b, c, d1, e1, f1,
  684.    a2, b, c, d2, e2, f2) fmtty_rel ->
  685.     ((f1, f2) eq -> (a1, a2) eq)
  686.   * ((a1, a2) eq -> (f1, f2) eq)
  687.   * ((e1, e2) eq -> (d1, d2) eq)
  688.   * ((d1, d2) eq -> (e1, e2) eq)
  689. = function
  690.   | End_of_fmtty ->
  691.     (fun Refl -> Refl),
  692.     (fun Refl -> Refl),
  693.     (fun Refl -> Refl),
  694.     (fun Refl -> Refl)
  695.   | Char_ty rest ->
  696. ‌    let fa, af, ed, de = fmtty_rel_det rest in
  697. ‌    (fun Refl -> let Refl = fa Refl in Refl),
  698. ‌    (fun Refl -> let Refl = af Refl in Refl),
  699.     ed, de
  700.   | String_ty rest ->
  701. ‌    let fa, af, ed, de = fmtty_rel_det rest in
  702. ‌    (fun Refl -> let Refl = fa Refl in Refl),
  703. ‌    (fun Refl -> let Refl = af Refl in Refl),
  704.     ed, de
  705.   | Int_ty rest ->
  706. ‌    let fa, af, ed, de = fmtty_rel_det rest in
  707. ‌    (fun Refl -> let Refl = fa Refl in Refl),
  708. ‌    (fun Refl -> let Refl = af Refl in Refl),
  709.     ed, de
  710.   | Int32_ty rest ->
  711. ‌    let fa, af, ed, de = fmtty_rel_det rest in
  712. ‌    (fun Refl -> let Refl = fa Refl in Refl),
  713. ‌    (fun Refl -> let Refl = af Refl in Refl),
  714.     ed, de
  715.   | Int64_ty rest ->
  716. ‌    let fa, af, ed, de = fmtty_rel_det rest in
  717. ‌    (fun Refl -> let Refl = fa Refl in Refl),
  718. ‌    (fun Refl -> let Refl = af Refl in Refl),
  719.     ed, de
  720.   | Nativeint_ty rest ->
  721. ‌    let fa, af, ed, de = fmtty_rel_det rest in
  722. ‌    (fun Refl -> let Refl = fa Refl in Refl),
  723. ‌    (fun Refl -> let Refl = af Refl in Refl),
  724.     ed, de
  725.   | Float_ty rest ->
  726. ‌    let fa, af, ed, de = fmtty_rel_det rest in
  727. ‌    (fun Refl -> let Refl = fa Refl in Refl),
  728. ‌    (fun Refl -> let Refl = af Refl in Refl),
  729.     ed, de
  730.   | Bool_ty rest ->
  731. ‌    let fa, af, ed, de = fmtty_rel_det rest in
  732. ‌    (fun Refl -> let Refl = fa Refl in Refl),
  733. ‌    (fun Refl -> let Refl = af Refl in Refl),
  734.     ed, de

  736.   | Theta_ty rest ->
  737. ‌    let fa, af, ed, de = fmtty_rel_det rest in
  738. ‌    (fun Refl -> let Refl = fa Refl in Refl),
  739. ‌    (fun Refl -> let Refl = af Refl in Refl),
  740.     ed, de
  741.   | Alpha_ty rest ->
  742. ‌    let fa, af, ed, de = fmtty_rel_det rest in
  743. ‌    (fun Refl -> let Refl = fa Refl in Refl),
  744. ‌    (fun Refl -> let Refl = af Refl in Refl),
  745.     ed, de
  746.   | Any_ty rest ->
  747. ‌    let fa, af, ed, de = fmtty_rel_det rest in
  748. ‌    (fun Refl -> let Refl = fa Refl in Refl),
  749. ‌    (fun Refl -> let Refl = af Refl in Refl),
  750.     ed, de
  751.   | Reader_ty rest ->
  752. ‌    let fa, af, ed, de = fmtty_rel_det rest in
  753. ‌    (fun Refl -> let Refl = fa Refl in Refl),
  754. ‌    (fun Refl -> let Refl = af Refl in Refl),
  755. ‌    (fun Refl -> let Refl = ed Refl in Refl),
  756. ‌    (fun Refl -> let Refl = de Refl in Refl)
  757.   | Ignored_reader_ty rest ->
  758. ‌    let fa, af, ed, de = fmtty_rel_det rest in
  759. ‌    (fun Refl -> let Refl = fa Refl in Refl),
  760. ‌    (fun Refl -> let Refl = af Refl in Refl),
  761. ‌    (fun Refl -> let Refl = ed Refl in Refl),
  762. ‌    (fun Refl -> let Refl = de Refl in Refl)
  763.   | Format_arg_ty (_ty, rest) ->
  764. ‌    let fa, af, ed, de = fmtty_rel_det rest in
  765. ‌    (fun Refl -> let Refl = fa Refl in Refl),
  766. ‌    (fun Refl -> let Refl = af Refl in Refl),
  767.     ed, de
  768.   | Format_subst_ty (ty1, ty2, rest) ->
  769. ‌    let fa, af, ed, de = fmtty_rel_det rest in
  770. ‌    let ty = trans (symm ty1) ty2 in
  771. ‌    let ag, ga, dj, jd = fmtty_rel_det ty in
  772. ‌‌    (fun Refl -> let Refl = fa Refl in let Refl = ag Refl in Refl),
  773. ‌‌    (fun Refl -> let Refl = ga Refl in let Refl = af Refl in Refl),
  774. ‌‌    (fun Refl -> let Refl = ed Refl in let Refl = dj Refl in Refl),
  775. ‌‌    (fun Refl -> let Refl = jd Refl in let Refl = de Refl in Refl)

  777. (* Precondition: we assume that the two fmtty_rel arguments have equal
  778.    values (at possibly distinct types); this invariant comes from the way
  779.    fmtty_rel witnesses are produced by the type-checker

  781.    The code below uses (assert false) when this assumption is broken. The
  782.    code pattern is the following:

  784.      | Foo x, Foo y ->
  785.        (* case where indeed both values
  786.           start with constructor Foo *)
  787.      | Foo _, _
  788.      | _, Foo _ ->
  789.        (* different head constructors: broken precondition *)
  790.        assert false
  791. *)
  792. ‌and trans : type
  793. ‌  a1 b1 c1 d1 e1 f1
  794.   a2 b2 c2 d2 e2 f2
  795.   a3 b3 c3 d3 e3 f3
  796. .
  797.    (a1, b1, c1, d1, e1, f1,
  798.     a2, b2, c2, d2, e2, f2) fmtty_rel
  799. -> (a2, b2, c2, d2, e2, f2,
  800.     a3, b3, c3, d3, e3, f3) fmtty_rel
  801. -> (a1, b1, c1, d1, e1, f1,
  802.     a3, b3, c3, d3, e3, f3) fmtty_rel
  803. = fun ty1 ty2 -> match ty1, ty2 with
  804.   | Char_ty rest1, Char_ty rest2 -> Char_ty (trans rest1 rest2)
  805.   | String_ty rest1, String_ty rest2 -> String_ty (trans rest1 rest2)
  806.   | Bool_ty rest1, Bool_ty rest2 -> Bool_ty (trans rest1 rest2)
  807.   | Int_ty rest1, Int_ty rest2 -> Int_ty (trans rest1 rest2)
  808.   | Int32_ty rest1, Int32_ty rest2 -> Int32_ty (trans rest1 rest2)
  809.   | Int64_ty rest1, Int64_ty rest2 -> Int64_ty (trans rest1 rest2)
  810.   | Nativeint_ty rest1, Nativeint_ty rest2 -> Nativeint_ty (trans rest1 rest2)
  811.   | Float_ty rest1, Float_ty rest2 -> Float_ty (trans rest1 rest2)

  813.   | Alpha_ty rest1, Alpha_ty rest2 -> Alpha_ty (trans rest1 rest2)
  814.   | Alpha_ty _, _ -> assert false
  815.   | _, Alpha_ty _ -> assert false

  817.   | Theta_ty rest1, Theta_ty rest2 -> Theta_ty (trans rest1 rest2)
  818.   | Theta_ty _, _ -> assert false
  819.   | _, Theta_ty _ -> assert false

  821.   | Any_ty rest1, Any_ty rest2 -> Any_ty (trans rest1 rest2)
  822.   | Any_ty _, _ -> assert false
  823.   | _, Any_ty _ -> assert false

  825.   | Reader_ty rest1, Reader_ty rest2 -> Reader_ty (trans rest1 rest2)
  826.   | Reader_ty _, _ -> assert false
  827.   | _, Reader_ty _ -> assert false

  829.   | Ignored_reader_ty rest1, Ignored_reader_ty rest2 ->
  830.     Ignored_reader_ty (trans rest1 rest2)
  831.   | Ignored_reader_ty _, _ -> assert false
  832.   | _, Ignored_reader_ty _ -> assert false

  834.   | Format_arg_ty (ty1, rest1), Format_arg_ty (ty2, rest2) ->
  835.     Format_arg_ty (trans ty1 ty2, trans rest1 rest2)
  836.   | Format_arg_ty _, _ -> assert false
  837.   | _, Format_arg_ty _ -> assert false

  839.   | Format_subst_ty (ty11, ty12, rest1),
  840.     Format_subst_ty (ty21, ty22, rest2) ->
  841. ‌    let ty = trans (symm ty12) ty21 in
  842.     let _, f2, _, f4 = fmtty_rel_det ty in
  843. ‌    let Refl = f2 Refl in
  844. ‌    let Refl = f4 Refl in
  845.     Format_subst_ty (ty11, ty22, trans rest1 rest2)
  846.   | Format_subst_ty _, _ -> assert false
  847.   | _, Format_subst_ty _ -> assert false

  849.   | End_of_fmtty, End_of_fmtty -> End_of_fmtty
  850.   | End_of_fmtty, _ -> assert false
  851.   | _, End_of_fmtty -> assert false

  853. ‌‌let rec fmtty_of_formatting_gen : type a b c d e f .
  854.   (a, b, c, d, e, f) formatting_gen ->
  855.     (a, b, c, d, e, f) fmtty =
  856. fun formatting_gen -> match formatting_gen with
  857.   | Open_tag (Format (fmt, _)) -> fmtty_of_fmt fmt
  858.   | Open_box (Format (fmt, _)) -> fmtty_of_fmt fmt

  860. (* Extract the type representation (an fmtty) of a format. *)
  861. ‌‌and fmtty_of_fmt : type a b c d e f .
  862.   (a, b, c, d, e, f) fmt -> (a, b, c, d, e, f) fmtty =
  863. fun fmtty -> match fmtty with
  864.   | String (pad, rest) ->
  865.     fmtty_of_padding_fmtty pad (String_ty (fmtty_of_fmt rest))
  866.   | Caml_string (pad, rest) ->
  867.     fmtty_of_padding_fmtty pad (String_ty (fmtty_of_fmt rest))

  869.   | Int (_, pad, prec, rest) ->
  870. ‌    let ty_rest = fmtty_of_fmt rest in
  871. ‌    let prec_ty = fmtty_of_precision_fmtty prec (Int_ty ty_rest) in
  872.     fmtty_of_padding_fmtty pad prec_ty
  873.   | Int32 (_, pad, prec, rest) ->
  874. ‌    let ty_rest = fmtty_of_fmt rest in
  875. ‌    let prec_ty = fmtty_of_precision_fmtty prec (Int32_ty ty_rest) in
  876.     fmtty_of_padding_fmtty pad prec_ty
  877.   | Nativeint (_, pad, prec, rest) ->
  878. ‌    let ty_rest = fmtty_of_fmt rest in
  879. ‌    let prec_ty = fmtty_of_precision_fmtty prec (Nativeint_ty ty_rest) in
  880.     fmtty_of_padding_fmtty pad prec_ty
  881.   | Int64 (_, pad, prec, rest) ->
  882. ‌    let ty_rest = fmtty_of_fmt rest in
  883. ‌    let prec_ty = fmtty_of_precision_fmtty prec (Int64_ty ty_rest) in
  884.     fmtty_of_padding_fmtty pad prec_ty
  885.   | Float (_, pad, prec, rest) ->
  886. ‌    let ty_rest = fmtty_of_fmt rest in
  887. ‌    let prec_ty = fmtty_of_precision_fmtty prec (Float_ty ty_rest) in
  888.     fmtty_of_padding_fmtty pad prec_ty

  890.   | Char rest                  -> Char_ty (fmtty_of_fmt rest)
  891.   | Caml_char rest             -> Char_ty (fmtty_of_fmt rest)
  892.   | Bool (pad, rest)           ->
  893.       fmtty_of_padding_fmtty pad (Bool_ty (fmtty_of_fmt rest))
  894.   | Alpha rest                 -> Alpha_ty (fmtty_of_fmt rest)
  895.   | Theta rest                 -> Theta_ty (fmtty_of_fmt rest)
  896.   | Custom (arity, _, rest)    -> fmtty_of_custom arity (fmtty_of_fmt rest)
  897.   | Reader rest                -> Reader_ty (fmtty_of_fmt rest)

  899.   | Format_arg (_, ty, rest) ->
  900.     Format_arg_ty (ty, fmtty_of_fmt rest)
  901.   | Format_subst (_, ty, rest) ->
  902.     Format_subst_ty (ty, ty, fmtty_of_fmt rest)

  904.   | Flush rest                 -> fmtty_of_fmt rest
  905.   | String_literal (_, rest)   -> fmtty_of_fmt rest
  906.   | Char_literal (_, rest)     -> fmtty_of_fmt rest

  908.   | Scan_char_set (_, _, rest) -> String_ty (fmtty_of_fmt rest)
  909.   | Scan_get_counter (_, rest) -> Int_ty (fmtty_of_fmt rest)
  910.   | Scan_next_char rest        -> Char_ty (fmtty_of_fmt rest)
  911.   | Ignored_param (ign, rest)  -> fmtty_of_ignored_format ign rest
  912.   | Formatting_lit (_, rest)   -> fmtty_of_fmt rest
  913.   | Formatting_gen (fmting_gen, rest)  ->
  914.     concat_fmtty (fmtty_of_formatting_gen fmting_gen) (fmtty_of_fmt rest)

  916.   | End_of_format              -> End_of_fmtty

  918. ‌‌and fmtty_of_custom : type x y a b c d e f .
  919.   (a, x, y) custom_arity -> (a, b, c, d, e, f) fmtty ->
  920.   (y, b, c, d, e, f) fmtty =
  921. fun arity fmtty -> match arity with
  922.   | Custom_zero -> fmtty
  923.   | Custom_succ arity -> Any_ty (fmtty_of_custom arity fmtty)

  925. (* Extract the fmtty of an ignored parameter followed by the rest of
  926.    the format. *)
  927. ‌‌and fmtty_of_ignored_format : type x y a b c d e f .
  928.     (a, b, c, d, y, x) ignored ->
  929.     (x, b, c, y, e, f) fmt ->
  930.     (a, b, c, d, e, f) fmtty =
  931. fun ign fmt -> match ign with
  932.   | Ignored_char                    -> fmtty_of_fmt fmt
  933.   | Ignored_caml_char               -> fmtty_of_fmt fmt
  934.   | Ignored_string _                -> fmtty_of_fmt fmt
  935.   | Ignored_caml_string _           -> fmtty_of_fmt fmt
  936.   | Ignored_int (_, _)              -> fmtty_of_fmt fmt
  937.   | Ignored_int32 (_, _)            -> fmtty_of_fmt fmt
  938.   | Ignored_nativeint (_, _)        -> fmtty_of_fmt fmt
  939.   | Ignored_int64 (_, _)            -> fmtty_of_fmt fmt
  940.   | Ignored_float (_, _)            -> fmtty_of_fmt fmt
  941.   | Ignored_bool _                  -> fmtty_of_fmt fmt
  942.   | Ignored_format_arg _            -> fmtty_of_fmt fmt
  943.   | Ignored_format_subst (_, fmtty) -> concat_fmtty fmtty (fmtty_of_fmt fmt)
  944.   | Ignored_reader                  -> Ignored_reader_ty (fmtty_of_fmt fmt)
  945.   | Ignored_scan_char_set _         -> fmtty_of_fmt fmt
  946.   | Ignored_scan_get_counter _      -> fmtty_of_fmt fmt
  947.   | Ignored_scan_next_char          -> fmtty_of_fmt fmt

  949. (* Add an Int_ty node if padding is taken as an extra argument (ex: "%*s"). *)
  950. ‌‌and fmtty_of_padding_fmtty : type x a b c d e f .
  951.     (x, a) padding -> (a, b, c, d, e, f) fmtty -> (x, b, c, d, e, f) fmtty =
  952.   fun pad fmtty -> match pad with
  953.     | No_padding    -> fmtty
  954.     | Lit_padding _ -> fmtty
  955.     | Arg_padding _ -> Int_ty fmtty

  957. (* Add an Int_ty node if precision is taken as an extra argument (ex: "%.*f").*)
  958. ‌‌and fmtty_of_precision_fmtty : type x a b c d e f .
  959.     (x, a) precision -> (a, b, c, d, e, f) fmtty -> (x, b, c, d, e, f) fmtty =
  960.   fun prec fmtty -> match prec with
  961.     | No_precision    -> fmtty
  962.     | Lit_precision _ -> fmtty
  963.     | Arg_precision   -> Int_ty fmtty

  965. (******************************************************************************)
  966.                             (* Format typing *)

  968. (* Exception raised when a format does not match a given format type. *)
  969. exception Type_mismatch

  971. (* Type a padding. *)
  972. (* Take an Int_ty from the fmtty if the integer should be kept as argument. *)
  973. (* Raise Type_mismatch in case of type mismatch. *)
  974. ‌‌let type_padding : type a b c d e f x y .
  975.     (x, y) padding -> (a, b, c, d, e, f) fmtty ->
  976.       (a, b, c, d, e, f) padding_fmtty_ebb =
  977. fun pad fmtty -> match pad, fmtty with
  978.   | No_padding, _ -> Padding_fmtty_EBB (No_padding, fmtty)
  979.   | Lit_padding (padty, w), _ -> Padding_fmtty_EBB (Lit_padding (padty,w),fmtty)
  980.   | Arg_padding padty, Int_ty rest -> Padding_fmtty_EBB (Arg_padding padty,rest)
  981.   | _ -> raise Type_mismatch

  983. (* Convert a (upadding, uprecision) to a (padding, precision). *)
  984. (* Take one or two Int_ty from the fmtty if needed. *)
  985. (* Raise Type_mismatch in case of type mismatch. *)
  986. ‌‌let type_padprec : type a b c d e f x y z .
  987.   (x, y) padding -> (y, z) precision -> (a, b, c, d, e, f) fmtty ->
  988.     (a, b, c, d, e, f) padprec_fmtty_ebb =
  989. fun pad prec fmtty -> match prec, type_padding pad fmtty with
  990.   | No_precision, Padding_fmtty_EBB (pad, rest) ->
  991.     Padprec_fmtty_EBB (pad, No_precision, rest)
  992.   | Lit_precision p, Padding_fmtty_EBB (pad, rest) ->
  993.     Padprec_fmtty_EBB (pad, Lit_precision p, rest)
  994.   | Arg_precision, Padding_fmtty_EBB (pad, Int_ty rest) ->
  995.     Padprec_fmtty_EBB (pad, Arg_precision, rest)
  996.   | _, Padding_fmtty_EBB (_, _) -> raise Type_mismatch

  998. (* Type a format according to an fmtty. *)
  999. (* If typing succeed, generate a copy of the format with the same
  1000.     type parameters as the fmtty. *)
  1001. (* Raise [Failure] with an error message in case of type mismatch. *)
  1002. ‌let rec type_format :
  1003. ‌  type a1 b1 c1 d1 e1 f1
  1004.        a2 b2 c2 d2 e2 f2  .
  1005.      (a1, b1, c1, d1, e1, f1) fmt
  1006.   -> (a2, b2, c2, d2, e2, f2) fmtty
  1007.   -> (a2, b2, c2, d2, e2, f2) fmt
  1008. = fun fmt fmtty -> match type_format_gen fmt fmtty with
  1009.   | Fmt_fmtty_EBB (fmt', End_of_fmtty) -> fmt'
  1010.   | _ -> raise Type_mismatch

  1012. ‌and type_format_gen :
  1013. ‌  type a1 b1 c1 d1 e1 f1
  1014.        a2 b2 c2 d2 e2 f2  .
  1015.      (a1, b1, c1, d1, e1, f1) fmt
  1016.   -> (a2, b2, c2, d2, e2, f2) fmtty
  1017.   -> (a2, b2, c2, d2, e2, f2) fmt_fmtty_ebb
  1018. = fun fmt fmtty -> match fmt, fmtty with
  1019.   | Char fmt_rest, Char_ty fmtty_rest ->
  1020. ‌    let Fmt_fmtty_EBB (fmt', fmtty') = type_format_gen fmt_rest fmtty_rest in
  1021.     Fmt_fmtty_EBB (Char fmt', fmtty')
  1022.   | Caml_char fmt_rest, Char_ty fmtty_rest ->
  1023. ‌    let Fmt_fmtty_EBB (fmt', fmtty') = type_format_gen fmt_rest fmtty_rest in
  1024.     Fmt_fmtty_EBB (Caml_char fmt', fmtty')
  1025.   | String (pad, fmt_rest), _ -> (
  1026.     match type_padding pad fmtty with
  1027.     | Padding_fmtty_EBB (pad, String_ty fmtty_rest) ->
  1028. ‌      let Fmt_fmtty_EBB (fmt', fmtty') = type_format_gen fmt_rest fmtty_rest in
  1029.       Fmt_fmtty_EBB (String (pad, fmt'), fmtty')
  1030.     | Padding_fmtty_EBB (_, _) -> raise Type_mismatch
  1031.   )
  1032.   | Caml_string (pad, fmt_rest), _ -> (
  1033.     match type_padding pad fmtty with
  1034.     | Padding_fmtty_EBB (pad, String_ty fmtty_rest) ->
  1035. ‌      let Fmt_fmtty_EBB (fmt', fmtty') = type_format_gen fmt_rest fmtty_rest in
  1036.       Fmt_fmtty_EBB (Caml_string (pad, fmt'), fmtty')
  1037.     | Padding_fmtty_EBB (_, _) -> raise Type_mismatch
  1038.   )
  1039.   | Int (iconv, pad, prec, fmt_rest), _ -> (
  1040.     match type_padprec pad prec fmtty with
  1041.     | Padprec_fmtty_EBB (pad, prec, Int_ty fmtty_rest) ->
  1042. ‌      let Fmt_fmtty_EBB (fmt', fmtty') = type_format_gen fmt_rest fmtty_rest in
  1043.       Fmt_fmtty_EBB (Int (iconv, pad, prec, fmt'), fmtty')
  1044.     | Padprec_fmtty_EBB (_, _, _) -> raise Type_mismatch
  1045.   )
  1046.   | Int32 (iconv, pad, prec, fmt_rest), _ -> (
  1047.     match type_padprec pad prec fmtty with
  1048.     | Padprec_fmtty_EBB (pad, prec, Int32_ty fmtty_rest) ->
  1049. ‌      let Fmt_fmtty_EBB (fmt', fmtty') = type_format_gen fmt_rest fmtty_rest in
  1050.       Fmt_fmtty_EBB (Int32 (iconv, pad, prec, fmt'), fmtty')
  1051.     | Padprec_fmtty_EBB (_, _, _) -> raise Type_mismatch
  1052.   )
  1053.   | Nativeint (iconv, pad, prec, fmt_rest), _ -> (
  1054.     match type_padprec pad prec fmtty with
  1055.     | Padprec_fmtty_EBB (pad, prec, Nativeint_ty fmtty_rest) ->
  1056. ‌      let Fmt_fmtty_EBB (fmt', fmtty') = type_format_gen fmt_rest fmtty_rest in
  1057.       Fmt_fmtty_EBB (Nativeint (iconv, pad, prec, fmt'), fmtty')
  1058.     | Padprec_fmtty_EBB (_, _, _) -> raise Type_mismatch
  1059.   )
  1060.   | Int64 (iconv, pad, prec, fmt_rest), _ -> (
  1061.     match type_padprec pad prec fmtty with
  1062.     | Padprec_fmtty_EBB (pad, prec, Int64_ty fmtty_rest) ->
  1063. ‌      let Fmt_fmtty_EBB (fmt', fmtty') = type_format_gen fmt_rest fmtty_rest in
  1064.       Fmt_fmtty_EBB (Int64 (iconv, pad, prec, fmt'), fmtty')
  1065.     | Padprec_fmtty_EBB (_, _, _) -> raise Type_mismatch
  1066.   )
  1067.   | Float (fconv, pad, prec, fmt_rest), _ -> (
  1068.     match type_padprec pad prec fmtty with
  1069.     | Padprec_fmtty_EBB (pad, prec, Float_ty fmtty_rest) ->
  1070. ‌      let Fmt_fmtty_EBB (fmt', fmtty') = type_format_gen fmt_rest fmtty_rest in
  1071.       Fmt_fmtty_EBB (Float (fconv, pad, prec, fmt'), fmtty')
  1072.     | Padprec_fmtty_EBB (_, _, _) -> raise Type_mismatch
  1073.   )
  1074.   | Bool (pad, fmt_rest), _ -> (
  1075.     match type_padding pad fmtty with
  1076.     | Padding_fmtty_EBB (pad, Bool_ty fmtty_rest) ->
  1077. ‌      let Fmt_fmtty_EBB (fmt', fmtty') = type_format_gen fmt_rest fmtty_rest in
  1078.       Fmt_fmtty_EBB (Bool (pad, fmt'), fmtty')
  1079.     | Padding_fmtty_EBB (_, _) -> raise Type_mismatch
  1080.   )
  1081.   | Flush fmt_rest, fmtty_rest ->
  1082. ‌    let Fmt_fmtty_EBB (fmt', fmtty') = type_format_gen fmt_rest fmtty_rest in
  1083.     Fmt_fmtty_EBB (Flush fmt', fmtty')

  1085.   | String_literal (str, fmt_rest), fmtty_rest ->
  1086. ‌    let Fmt_fmtty_EBB (fmt', fmtty') = type_format_gen fmt_rest fmtty_rest in
  1087.     Fmt_fmtty_EBB (String_literal (str, fmt'), fmtty')
  1088.   | Char_literal (chr, fmt_rest), fmtty_rest ->
  1089. ‌    let Fmt_fmtty_EBB (fmt', fmtty') = type_format_gen fmt_rest fmtty_rest in
  1090.     Fmt_fmtty_EBB (Char_literal (chr, fmt'), fmtty')

  1092.   | Format_arg (pad_opt, sub_fmtty, fmt_rest),
  1093.     Format_arg_ty (sub_fmtty', fmtty_rest) ->
  1094.     if Fmtty_EBB sub_fmtty <> Fmtty_EBB sub_fmtty' then raise Type_mismatch;
  1095. ‌    let Fmt_fmtty_EBB (fmt', fmtty') = type_format_gen fmt_rest fmtty_rest in
  1096.     Fmt_fmtty_EBB (Format_arg (pad_opt, sub_fmtty', fmt'), fmtty')
  1097.   | Format_subst (pad_opt, sub_fmtty, fmt_rest),
  1098.     Format_subst_ty (sub_fmtty1, _sub_fmtty2, fmtty_rest) ->
  1099.     if Fmtty_EBB (erase_rel sub_fmtty) <> Fmtty_EBB (erase_rel sub_fmtty1) then
  1100.       raise Type_mismatch;
  1101. ‌    let Fmt_fmtty_EBB (fmt', fmtty') =
  1102.       type_format_gen fmt_rest (erase_rel fmtty_rest)
  1103.     in
  1104.     Fmt_fmtty_EBB (Format_subst (pad_opt, sub_fmtty1, fmt'), fmtty')
  1105.   (* Printf and Format specific constructors: *)
  1106.   | Alpha fmt_rest, Alpha_ty fmtty_rest ->
  1107. ‌    let Fmt_fmtty_EBB (fmt', fmtty') = type_format_gen fmt_rest fmtty_rest in
  1108.     Fmt_fmtty_EBB (Alpha fmt', fmtty')
  1109.   | Theta fmt_rest, Theta_ty fmtty_rest ->
  1110. ‌    let Fmt_fmtty_EBB (fmt', fmtty') = type_format_gen fmt_rest fmtty_rest in
  1111.     Fmt_fmtty_EBB (Theta fmt', fmtty')

  1113.   (* Format specific constructors: *)
  1114.   | Formatting_lit (formatting_lit, fmt_rest), fmtty_rest ->
  1115. ‌    let Fmt_fmtty_EBB (fmt', fmtty') = type_format_gen fmt_rest fmtty_rest in
  1116.     Fmt_fmtty_EBB (Formatting_lit (formatting_lit, fmt'), fmtty')
  1117.   | Formatting_gen (formatting_gen, fmt_rest), fmtty_rest ->
  1118.     type_formatting_gen formatting_gen fmt_rest fmtty_rest

  1120.   (* Scanf specific constructors: *)
  1121.   | Reader fmt_rest, Reader_ty fmtty_rest ->
  1122. ‌    let Fmt_fmtty_EBB (fmt', fmtty') = type_format_gen fmt_rest fmtty_rest in
  1123.     Fmt_fmtty_EBB (Reader fmt', fmtty')
  1124.   | Scan_char_set (width_opt, char_set, fmt_rest), String_ty fmtty_rest ->
  1125. ‌    let Fmt_fmtty_EBB (fmt', fmtty') = type_format_gen fmt_rest fmtty_rest in
  1126.     Fmt_fmtty_EBB (Scan_char_set (width_opt, char_set, fmt'), fmtty')
  1127.   | Scan_get_counter (counter, fmt_rest), Int_ty fmtty_rest ->
  1128. ‌    let Fmt_fmtty_EBB (fmt', fmtty') = type_format_gen fmt_rest fmtty_rest in
  1129.     Fmt_fmtty_EBB (Scan_get_counter (counter, fmt'), fmtty')
  1130.   | Ignored_param (ign, rest), fmtty_rest ->
  1131.     type_ignored_param ign rest fmtty_rest

  1133.   | End_of_format, fmtty_rest -> Fmt_fmtty_EBB (End_of_format, fmtty_rest)

  1135.   | _ -> raise Type_mismatch

  1137. ‌‌and type_formatting_gen : type a1 a3 b1 b3 c1 c3 d1 d3 e1 e2 e3 f1 f2 f3 .
  1138.     (a1, b1, c1, d1, e1, f1) formatting_gen ->
  1139.     (f1, b1, c1, e1, e2, f2) fmt ->
  1140.     (a3, b3, c3, d3, e3, f3) fmtty ->
  1141.     (a3, b3, c3, d3, e3, f3) fmt_fmtty_ebb =
  1142. fun formatting_gen fmt0 fmtty0 -> match formatting_gen with
  1143.   | Open_tag (Format (fmt1, str)) ->
  1144. ‌    let Fmt_fmtty_EBB (fmt2, fmtty2) = type_format_gen fmt1 fmtty0 in
  1145. ‌    let Fmt_fmtty_EBB (fmt3, fmtty3) = type_format_gen fmt0 fmtty2 in
  1146.     Fmt_fmtty_EBB (Formatting_gen (Open_tag (Format (fmt2, str)), fmt3), fmtty3)
  1147.   | Open_box (Format (fmt1, str)) ->
  1148. ‌    let Fmt_fmtty_EBB (fmt2, fmtty2) = type_format_gen fmt1 fmtty0 in
  1149. ‌    let Fmt_fmtty_EBB (fmt3, fmtty3) = type_format_gen fmt0 fmtty2 in
  1150.     Fmt_fmtty_EBB (Formatting_gen (Open_box (Format (fmt2, str)), fmt3), fmtty3)

  1152. (* Type an Ignored_param node according to an fmtty. *)
  1153. ‌‌and type_ignored_param : type p q x y z t u v a b c d e f .
  1154.     (x, y, z, t, q, p) ignored ->
  1155.     (p, y, z, q, u, v) fmt ->
  1156.     (a, b, c, d, e, f) fmtty ->
  1157.     (a, b, c, d, e, f) fmt_fmtty_ebb =
  1158. fun ign fmt fmtty -> match ign with
  1159.   | Ignored_char               as ign' -> type_ignored_param_one ign' fmt fmtty
  1160.   | Ignored_caml_char          as ign' -> type_ignored_param_one ign' fmt fmtty
  1161.   | Ignored_string _           as ign' -> type_ignored_param_one ign' fmt fmtty
  1162.   | Ignored_caml_string _      as ign' -> type_ignored_param_one ign' fmt fmtty
  1163.   | Ignored_int _              as ign' -> type_ignored_param_one ign' fmt fmtty
  1164.   | Ignored_int32 _            as ign' -> type_ignored_param_one ign' fmt fmtty
  1165.   | Ignored_nativeint _        as ign' -> type_ignored_param_one ign' fmt fmtty
  1166.   | Ignored_int64 _            as ign' -> type_ignored_param_one ign' fmt fmtty
  1167.   | Ignored_float _            as ign' -> type_ignored_param_one ign' fmt fmtty
  1168.   | Ignored_bool _             as ign' -> type_ignored_param_one ign' fmt fmtty
  1169.   | Ignored_scan_char_set _    as ign' -> type_ignored_param_one ign' fmt fmtty
  1170.   | Ignored_scan_get_counter _ as ign' -> type_ignored_param_one ign' fmt fmtty
  1171.   | Ignored_scan_next_char     as ign' -> type_ignored_param_one ign' fmt fmtty
  1172.   | Ignored_format_arg (pad_opt, sub_fmtty) ->
  1173.     type_ignored_param_one (Ignored_format_arg (pad_opt, sub_fmtty)) fmt fmtty
  1174.   | Ignored_format_subst (pad_opt, sub_fmtty) ->
  1175. ‌    let Fmtty_fmt_EBB (sub_fmtty', Fmt_fmtty_EBB (fmt', fmtty')) =
  1176.       type_ignored_format_substitution sub_fmtty fmt fmtty in
  1177.     Fmt_fmtty_EBB (Ignored_param (Ignored_format_subst (pad_opt, sub_fmtty'),
  1178.                                   fmt'),
  1179.                    fmtty')
  1180.   | Ignored_reader -> (
  1181.     match fmtty with
  1182.     | Ignored_reader_ty fmtty_rest ->
  1183. ‌      let Fmt_fmtty_EBB (fmt', fmtty') = type_format_gen fmt fmtty_rest in
  1184.       Fmt_fmtty_EBB (Ignored_param (Ignored_reader, fmt'), fmtty')
  1185.     | _ -> raise Type_mismatch
  1186.   )

  1188. ‌‌and type_ignored_param_one : type a1 a2 b1 b2 c1 c2 d1 d2 e1 e2 f1 f2 .
  1189.     (a2, b2, c2, d2, d2, a2) ignored ->
  1190.     (a1, b1, c1, d1, e1, f1) fmt ->
  1191.     (a2, b2, c2, d2, e2, f2) fmtty ->
  1192.     (a2, b2, c2, d2, e2, f2) fmt_fmtty_ebb
  1193. = fun ign fmt fmtty ->
  1194. ‌  let Fmt_fmtty_EBB (fmt', fmtty') = type_format_gen fmt fmtty in
  1195.   Fmt_fmtty_EBB (Ignored_param (ign, fmt'), fmtty')

  1197. (* Typing of the complex case: "%_(...%)". *)
  1198. ‌‌and type_ignored_format_substitution : type w x y z p s t u a b c d e f .
  1199.     (w, x, y, z, s, p) fmtty ->
  1200.     (p, x, y, s, t, u) fmt ->
  1201.     (a, b, c, d, e, f) fmtty -> (a, b, c, d, e, f) fmtty_fmt_ebb =
  1202. fun sub_fmtty fmt fmtty -> match sub_fmtty, fmtty with
  1203.   | Char_ty sub_fmtty_rest, Char_ty fmtty_rest ->
  1204. ‌    let Fmtty_fmt_EBB (sub_fmtty_rest', fmt') =
  1205.       type_ignored_format_substitution sub_fmtty_rest fmt fmtty_rest in
  1206.     Fmtty_fmt_EBB (Char_ty sub_fmtty_rest', fmt')
  1207.   | String_ty sub_fmtty_rest, String_ty fmtty_rest ->
  1208. ‌    let Fmtty_fmt_EBB (sub_fmtty_rest', fmt') =
  1209.       type_ignored_format_substitution sub_fmtty_rest fmt fmtty_rest in
  1210.     Fmtty_fmt_EBB (String_ty sub_fmtty_rest', fmt')
  1211.   | Int_ty sub_fmtty_rest, Int_ty fmtty_rest ->
  1212. ‌    let Fmtty_fmt_EBB (sub_fmtty_rest', fmt') =
  1213.       type_ignored_format_substitution sub_fmtty_rest fmt fmtty_rest in
  1214.     Fmtty_fmt_EBB (Int_ty sub_fmtty_rest', fmt')
  1215.   | Int32_ty sub_fmtty_rest, Int32_ty fmtty_rest ->
  1216. ‌    let Fmtty_fmt_EBB (sub_fmtty_rest', fmt') =
  1217.       type_ignored_format_substitution sub_fmtty_rest fmt fmtty_rest in
  1218.     Fmtty_fmt_EBB (Int32_ty sub_fmtty_rest', fmt')
  1219.   | Nativeint_ty sub_fmtty_rest, Nativeint_ty fmtty_rest ->
  1220. ‌    let Fmtty_fmt_EBB (sub_fmtty_rest', fmt') =
  1221.       type_ignored_format_substitution sub_fmtty_rest fmt fmtty_rest in
  1222.     Fmtty_fmt_EBB (Nativeint_ty sub_fmtty_rest', fmt')
  1223.   | Int64_ty sub_fmtty_rest, Int64_ty fmtty_rest ->
  1224. ‌    let Fmtty_fmt_EBB (sub_fmtty_rest', fmt') =
  1225.       type_ignored_format_substitution sub_fmtty_rest fmt fmtty_rest in
  1226.     Fmtty_fmt_EBB (Int64_ty sub_fmtty_rest', fmt')
  1227.   | Float_ty sub_fmtty_rest, Float_ty fmtty_rest ->
  1228. ‌    let Fmtty_fmt_EBB (sub_fmtty_rest', fmt') =
  1229.       type_ignored_format_substitution sub_fmtty_rest fmt fmtty_rest in
  1230.     Fmtty_fmt_EBB (Float_ty sub_fmtty_rest', fmt')
  1231.   | Bool_ty sub_fmtty_rest, Bool_ty fmtty_rest ->
  1232. ‌    let Fmtty_fmt_EBB (sub_fmtty_rest', fmt') =
  1233.       type_ignored_format_substitution sub_fmtty_rest fmt fmtty_rest in
  1234.     Fmtty_fmt_EBB (Bool_ty sub_fmtty_rest', fmt')
  1235.   | Alpha_ty sub_fmtty_rest, Alpha_ty fmtty_rest ->
  1236. ‌    let Fmtty_fmt_EBB (sub_fmtty_rest', fmt') =
  1237.       type_ignored_format_substitution sub_fmtty_rest fmt fmtty_rest in
  1238.     Fmtty_fmt_EBB (Alpha_ty sub_fmtty_rest', fmt')
  1239.   | Theta_ty sub_fmtty_rest, Theta_ty fmtty_rest ->
  1240. ‌    let Fmtty_fmt_EBB (sub_fmtty_rest', fmt') =
  1241.       type_ignored_format_substitution sub_fmtty_rest fmt fmtty_rest in
  1242.     Fmtty_fmt_EBB (Theta_ty sub_fmtty_rest', fmt')
  1243.   | Reader_ty sub_fmtty_rest, Reader_ty fmtty_rest ->
  1244. ‌    let Fmtty_fmt_EBB (sub_fmtty_rest', fmt') =
  1245.       type_ignored_format_substitution sub_fmtty_rest fmt fmtty_rest in
  1246.     Fmtty_fmt_EBB (Reader_ty sub_fmtty_rest', fmt')
  1247.   | Ignored_reader_ty sub_fmtty_rest, Ignored_reader_ty fmtty_rest ->
  1248. ‌    let Fmtty_fmt_EBB (sub_fmtty_rest', fmt') =
  1249.       type_ignored_format_substitution sub_fmtty_rest fmt fmtty_rest in
  1250.     Fmtty_fmt_EBB (Ignored_reader_ty sub_fmtty_rest', fmt')

  1252.   | Format_arg_ty (sub2_fmtty, sub_fmtty_rest),
  1253.     Format_arg_ty (sub2_fmtty', fmtty_rest) ->
  1254.     if Fmtty_EBB sub2_fmtty <> Fmtty_EBB sub2_fmtty' then raise Type_mismatch;
  1255. ‌    let Fmtty_fmt_EBB (sub_fmtty_rest', fmt') =
  1256.       type_ignored_format_substitution sub_fmtty_rest fmt fmtty_rest in
  1257.     Fmtty_fmt_EBB (Format_arg_ty (sub2_fmtty', sub_fmtty_rest'), fmt')
  1258.   | Format_subst_ty (sub1_fmtty,  sub2_fmtty,  sub_fmtty_rest),
  1259.     Format_subst_ty (sub1_fmtty', sub2_fmtty', fmtty_rest) ->
  1260.     (* TODO define Fmtty_rel_EBB to remove those erase_rel *)
  1261.     if Fmtty_EBB (erase_rel sub1_fmtty) <> Fmtty_EBB (erase_rel sub1_fmtty')
  1262.     then raise Type_mismatch;
  1263.     if Fmtty_EBB (erase_rel sub2_fmtty) <> Fmtty_EBB (erase_rel sub2_fmtty')
  1264.     then raise Type_mismatch;
  1265. ‌    let sub_fmtty' = trans (symm sub1_fmtty') sub2_fmtty' in
  1266.     let _, f2, _, f4 = fmtty_rel_det sub_fmtty' in
  1267. ‌    let Refl = f2 Refl in
  1268. ‌    let Refl = f4 Refl in
  1269. ‌    let Fmtty_fmt_EBB (sub_fmtty_rest', fmt') =
  1270.       type_ignored_format_substitution (erase_rel sub_fmtty_rest) fmt fmtty_rest
  1271.     in
  1272.     Fmtty_fmt_EBB (Format_subst_ty (sub1_fmtty', sub2_fmtty',
  1273.                                     symm sub_fmtty_rest'),
  1274.                    fmt')
  1275.   | End_of_fmtty, fmtty ->
  1276.     Fmtty_fmt_EBB (End_of_fmtty, type_format_gen fmt fmtty)
  1277.   | _ -> raise Type_mismatch

  1279. (* This implementation of `recast` is a bit disappointing. The
  1280.    invariant provided by the type are very strong: the input format's
  1281.    type is in relation to the output type's as witnessed by the
  1282.    fmtty_rel argument. One would at first expect this function to be
  1283.    total, and implementable by exhaustive pattern matching. Instead,
  1284.    we reuse the highly partial and much less well-defined function
  1285.    `type_format` that has lost all knowledge of the correspondence
  1286.    between the argument's types.

  1288.    Besides the fact that this function reuses a lot of the
  1289.    `type_format` logic (eg.: seeing Int_ty in the fmtty parameter does
  1290.    not let you match on Int only, as you may in fact have Float
  1291.    (Arg_padding, ...) ("%.*d") beginning with an Int_ty), it is also
  1292.    a partial function, because the typing information in a format is
  1293.    not quite enough to reconstruct it unambiguously. For example, the
  1294.    format types of "%d%_r" and "%_r%d" have the same format6
  1295.    parameters, but they are not at all exchangeable, and putting one
  1296.    in place of the other must result in a dynamic failure.

  1298.    Given that:
  1299.    - we'd have to duplicate a lot of non-trivial typing logic from type_format
  1300.    - this wouldn't even eliminate (all) the dynamic failures
  1301.    we decided to just reuse type_format directly for now.
  1302. *)
  1303. ‌let recast :
  1304. ‌  type a1 b1 c1 d1 e1 f1
  1305.        a2 b2 c2 d2 e2 f2
  1306.   .
  1307.      (a1, b1, c1, d1, e1, f1) fmt
  1308.   -> (a1, b1, c1, d1, e1, f1,
  1309.       a2, b2, c2, d2, e2, f2) fmtty_rel
  1310.   -> (a2, b2, c2, d2, e2, f2) fmt
  1311. = fun fmt fmtty ->
  1312.   type_format fmt (erase_rel (symm fmtty))

  1314. (******************************************************************************)
  1315.                              (* Printing tools *)

  1317. (* Add padding spaces around a string. *)
  1318. ‌let fix_padding padty width str =
  1319.   let len = String.length str in
  1320.   let width, padty =
  1321.     abs width,
  1322.     (* while literal padding widths are always non-negative,
  1323.        dynamically-set widths (Arg_padding, eg. %*d) may be negative;
  1324.        we interpret those as specifying a padding-to-the-left; this
  1325.        means that '0' may get dropped even if it was explicitly set,
  1326.        but:
  1327.        - this is what the legacy implementation does, and
  1328.          we preserve compatibility if possible
  1329.        - we could only signal this issue by failing at runtime,
  1330.          which is not very nice... *)
  1331.     if width < 0 then Left else padty in
  1332.   if width <= len then str else
  1333. ‌    let res = Bytes.make width (if padty = Zeros then '0' else ' ') in
  1334.     begin match padty with
  1335.     | Left  -> String.blit str 0 res 0 len
  1336.     | Right -> String.blit str 0 res (width - len) len
  1337.     | Zeros when len > 0 && (str.[0] = '+' || str.[0] = '-' || str.[0] = ' ') ->
  1338.       Bytes.set res 0 str.[0];
  1339.       String.blit str 1 res (width - len + 1) (len - 1)
  1340.     | Zeros when len > 1 && str.[0] = '0' && (str.[1] = 'x' || str.[1] = 'X') ->
  1341.       Bytes.set res 1 str.[1];
  1342.       String.blit str 2 res (width - len + 2) (len - 2)
  1343.     | Zeros ->
  1344.       String.blit str 0 res (width - len) len
  1345.     end;
  1346.     Bytes.unsafe_to_string res

  1348. (* Add '0' padding to int, int32, nativeint or int64 string representation. *)
  1349. ‌let fix_int_precision prec str =
  1350.   let prec = abs prec in
  1351.   let len = String.length str in
  1352.   match str.[0] with
  1353.   | ('+' | '-' | ' ') as c when prec + 1 > len ->
  1354.     let res = Bytes.make (prec + 1) '0' in
  1355.     Bytes.set res 0 c;
  1356.     String.blit str 1 res (prec - len + 2) (len - 1);
  1357.     Bytes.unsafe_to_string res
  1358.   | '0' when prec + 2 > len && len > 1 && (str.[1] = 'x' || str.[1] = 'X') ->
  1359.     let res = Bytes.make (prec + 2) '0' in
  1360.     Bytes.set res 1 str.[1];
  1361.     String.blit str 2 res (prec - len + 4) (len - 2);
  1362.     Bytes.unsafe_to_string res
  1363.   | '0' .. '9' | 'a' .. 'f' | 'A' .. 'F' when prec > len ->
  1364.     let res = Bytes.make prec '0' in
  1365.     String.blit str 0 res (prec - len) len;
  1366.     Bytes.unsafe_to_string res
  1367.   | _ ->
  1368.     str

  1370. (* Escape a string according to the OCaml lexing convention. *)
  1371. ‌let string_to_caml_string str =
  1372.   let str = String.escaped str in
  1373.   let l = String.length str in
  1374.   let res = Bytes.make (l + 2) '\"' in
  1375.   String.unsafe_blit str 0 res 1 l;
  1376.   Bytes.unsafe_to_string res

  1378. (* Generate the format_int/int32/nativeint/int64 first argument
  1379.    from an int_conv. *)
  1380. ‌let format_of_iconv = function
  1381.   | Int_d | Int_Cd -> "%d" | Int_pd -> "%+d" | Int_sd -> "% d"
  1382.   | Int_i | Int_Ci -> "%i" | Int_pi -> "%+i" | Int_si -> "% i"
  1383.   | Int_x -> "%x" | Int_Cx -> "%#x"
  1384.   | Int_X -> "%X" | Int_CX -> "%#X"
  1385.   | Int_o -> "%o" | Int_Co -> "%#o"
  1386.   | Int_u | Int_Cu -> "%u"

  1388. ‌let format_of_iconvL = function
  1389.   | Int_d | Int_Cd -> "%Ld" | Int_pd -> "%+Ld" | Int_sd -> "% Ld"
  1390.   | Int_i | Int_Ci -> "%Li" | Int_pi -> "%+Li" | Int_si -> "% Li"
  1391.   | Int_x -> "%Lx" | Int_Cx -> "%#Lx"
  1392.   | Int_X -> "%LX" | Int_CX -> "%#LX"
  1393.   | Int_o -> "%Lo" | Int_Co -> "%#Lo"
  1394.   | Int_u | Int_Cu -> "%Lu"

  1396. ‌let format_of_iconvl = function
  1397.   | Int_d | Int_Cd -> "%ld" | Int_pd -> "%+ld" | Int_sd -> "% ld"
  1398.   | Int_i | Int_Ci -> "%li" | Int_pi -> "%+li" | Int_si -> "% li"
  1399.   | Int_x -> "%lx" | Int_Cx -> "%#lx"
  1400.   | Int_X -> "%lX" | Int_CX -> "%#lX"
  1401.   | Int_o -> "%lo" | Int_Co -> "%#lo"
  1402.   | Int_u | Int_Cu -> "%lu"

  1404. ‌let format_of_iconvn = function
  1405.   | Int_d | Int_Cd -> "%nd" | Int_pd -> "%+nd" | Int_sd -> "% nd"
  1406.   | Int_i | Int_Ci -> "%ni" | Int_pi -> "%+ni" | Int_si -> "% ni"
  1407.   | Int_x -> "%nx" | Int_Cx -> "%#nx"
  1408.   | Int_X -> "%nX" | Int_CX -> "%#nX"
  1409.   | Int_o -> "%no" | Int_Co -> "%#no"
  1410.   | Int_u | Int_Cu -> "%nu"

  1412. (* Generate the format_float first argument from a float_conv. *)
  1413. ‌let format_of_fconv fconv prec =
  1414.     let prec = abs prec in
  1415.     let symb = char_of_fconv ~cF:'g' fconv in
  1416.     let buf = buffer_create 16 in
  1417.     buffer_add_char buf '%';
  1418.     bprint_fconv_flag buf fconv;
  1419.     buffer_add_char buf '.';
  1420.     buffer_add_string buf (Int.to_string prec);
  1421.     buffer_add_char buf symb;
  1422.     buffer_contents buf

  1424. ‌let transform_int_alt iconv s =
  1425.   match iconv with
  1426.   | Int_Cd | Int_Ci | Int_Cu ->
  1427.     let digits =
  1428.       let n = ref 0 in
  1429.       for i = 0 to String.length s - 1 do
  1430.         match String.unsafe_get s i with
  1431.         | '0'..'9' -> incr n
  1432.         | _ -> ()
  1433.       done;
  1434.       !n
  1435.     in
  1436.     let buf = Bytes.create (String.length s + (digits - 1) / 3) in
  1437.     let pos = ref 0 in
  1438.     let put c = Bytes.set buf !pos c; incr pos in
  1439.     let left = ref ((digits - 1) mod 3 + 1) in
  1440.     for i = 0 to String.length s - 1 do
  1441.       match String.unsafe_get s i with
  1442.       | '0'..'9' as c ->
  1443.           if !left = 0 then (put '_'; left := 3); decr left; put c
  1444.       | c -> put c
  1445.     done;
  1446.     Bytes.unsafe_to_string buf
  1447.   | _ -> s

  1449. (* Convert an integer to a string according to a conversion. *)
  1450. ‌let convert_int iconv n =
  1451.   transform_int_alt iconv (format_int (format_of_iconv iconv) n)
  1452. ‌let convert_int32 iconv n =
  1453.   transform_int_alt iconv (format_int32 (format_of_iconvl iconv) n)
  1454. ‌let convert_nativeint iconv n =
  1455.   transform_int_alt iconv (format_nativeint (format_of_iconvn iconv) n)
  1456. ‌let convert_int64 iconv n =
  1457.   transform_int_alt iconv (format_int64 (format_of_iconvL iconv) n)

  1459. (* Convert a float to string. *)
  1460. (* Fix special case of "OCaml float format". *)
  1461. ‌let convert_float fconv prec x =
  1462.   let hex () =
  1463.     let sign =
  1464.       match fst fconv with
  1465.       | Float_flag_p -> '+'
  1466.       | Float_flag_s -> ' '
  1467.       | _ -> '-' in
  1468.     hexstring_of_float x prec sign in
  1469.   let add_dot_if_needed str =
  1470.     let len = String.length str in
  1471.     let rec is_valid i =
  1472.       if i = len then false else
  1473.         match str.[i] with
  1474.         | '.' | 'e' | 'E' -> true
  1475.         | _ -> is_valid (i + 1) in
  1476.     if is_valid 0 then str else str ^ "." in
  1477. ‌  let caml_special_val str = match classify_float x with
  1478.     | FP_normal | FP_subnormal | FP_zero -> str
  1479.     | FP_infinite -> if x < 0.0 then "neg_infinity" else "infinity"
  1480.     | FP_nan -> "nan" in
  1481.   match snd fconv with
  1482.   | Float_h -> hex ()
  1483.   | Float_H -> String.uppercase_ascii (hex ())
  1484.   | Float_CF -> caml_special_val (hex ())
  1485.   | Float_F ->
  1486. ‌    let str = format_float (format_of_fconv fconv prec) x in
  1487.     caml_special_val (add_dot_if_needed str)
  1488.   | Float_f | Float_e | Float_E | Float_g | Float_G ->
  1489.     format_float (format_of_fconv fconv prec) x

  1491. (* Convert a char to a string according to the OCaml lexical convention. *)
  1492. ‌let format_caml_char c =
  1493.   let str = Char.escaped c in
  1494.   let l = String.length str in
  1495.   let res = Bytes.make (l + 2) '\'' in
  1496.   String.unsafe_blit str 0 res 1 l;
  1497.   Bytes.unsafe_to_string res

  1499. (* Convert a format type to string *)
  1500. ‌let string_of_fmtty fmtty =
  1501.   let buf = buffer_create 16 in
  1502.   bprint_fmtty buf fmtty;
  1503.   buffer_contents buf

  1505. (******************************************************************************)
  1506.                         (* Generic printing function *)

  1508. (* Make a generic printing function. *)
  1509. (* Used to generate Printf and Format printing functions. *)
  1510. (* Parameters:
  1511.      k: a continuation finally applied to the output stream and the accumulator.
  1512.      o: the output stream (see k, %a and %t).
  1513.      acc: rev list of printing entities (string, char, flush, formatting, ...).
  1514.      fmt: the format. *)
  1515. ‌‌let rec make_printf : type a b c d e f .
  1516.     ((b, c) acc -> f) -> (b, c) acc ->
  1517.     (a, b, c, d, e, f) fmt -> a =
  1518. fun k acc fmt -> match fmt with
  1519.   | Char rest ->
  1520.     fun c ->
  1521. ‌      let new_acc = Acc_data_char (acc, c) in
  1522.       make_printf k new_acc rest
  1523.   | Caml_char rest ->
  1524.     fun c ->
  1525. ‌      let new_acc = Acc_data_string (acc, format_caml_char c) in
  1526.       make_printf k new_acc rest
  1527.   | String (pad, rest) ->
  1528.     make_padding k acc rest pad (fun str -> str)
  1529.   | Caml_string (pad, rest) ->
  1530.     make_padding k acc rest pad string_to_caml_string
  1531.   | Int (iconv, pad, prec, rest) ->
  1532.     make_int_padding_precision k acc rest pad prec convert_int iconv
  1533.   | Int32 (iconv, pad, prec, rest) ->
  1534.     make_int_padding_precision k acc rest pad prec convert_int32 iconv
  1535.   | Nativeint (iconv, pad, prec, rest) ->
  1536.     make_int_padding_precision k acc rest pad prec convert_nativeint iconv
  1537.   | Int64 (iconv, pad, prec, rest) ->
  1538.     make_int_padding_precision k acc rest pad prec convert_int64 iconv
  1539.   | Float (fconv, pad, prec, rest) ->
  1540.     make_float_padding_precision k acc rest pad prec fconv
  1541.   | Bool (pad, rest) ->
  1542.     make_padding k acc rest pad string_of_bool
  1543.   | Alpha rest ->
  1544.     fun f x -> make_printf k (Acc_delay (acc, fun o -> f o x)) rest
  1545.   | Theta rest ->
  1546.     fun f -> make_printf k (Acc_delay (acc, f)) rest
  1547.   | Custom (arity, f, rest) ->
  1548.     make_custom k acc rest arity (f ())
  1549.   | Reader _ ->
  1550.     (* This case is impossible, by typing of formats. *)
  1551.     (* Indeed, since printf and co. take a format4 as argument, the 'd and 'e
  1552.        type parameters of fmt are obviously equals. The Reader is the
  1553.        only constructor which touch 'd and 'e type parameters of the format
  1554.        type, it adds an (->) to the 'd parameters. Consequently, a format4
  1555.        cannot contain a Reader node, except in the sub-format associated to
  1556.        an %{...%}. It's not a problem because make_printf do not call
  1557.        itself recursively on the sub-format associated to %{...%}. *)
  1558.     assert false
  1559.   | Flush rest ->
  1560.     make_printf k (Acc_flush acc) rest

  1562.   | String_literal (str, rest) ->
  1563.     make_printf k (Acc_string_literal (acc, str)) rest
  1564.   | Char_literal (chr, rest) ->
  1565.     make_printf k (Acc_char_literal (acc, chr)) rest

  1567.   | Format_arg (_, sub_fmtty, rest) ->
  1568. ‌    let ty = string_of_fmtty sub_fmtty in
  1569.     (fun str ->
  1570.       ignore str;
  1571.       make_printf k (Acc_data_string (acc, ty)) rest)
  1572.   | Format_subst (_, fmtty, rest) ->
  1573.     fun (Format (fmt, _)) -> make_printf k acc
  1574.       (concat_fmt (recast fmt fmtty) rest)

  1576.   | Scan_char_set (_, _, rest) ->
  1577. ‌    let new_acc = Acc_invalid_arg (acc, "Printf: bad conversion %[") in
  1578.     fun _ -> make_printf k new_acc rest
  1579.   | Scan_get_counter (_, rest) ->
  1580.     (* This case should be refused for Printf. *)
  1581.     (* Accepted for backward compatibility. *)
  1582.     (* Interpret %l, %n and %L as %u. *)
  1583.     fun n ->
  1584. ‌      let new_acc = Acc_data_string (acc, format_int "%u" n) in
  1585.       make_printf k new_acc rest
  1586.   | Scan_next_char rest ->
  1587.     fun c ->
  1588. ‌      let new_acc = Acc_data_char (acc, c) in
  1589.       make_printf k new_acc rest
  1590.   | Ignored_param (ign, rest) ->
  1591.     make_ignored_param k acc ign rest

  1593.   | Formatting_lit (fmting_lit, rest) ->
  1594.     make_printf k (Acc_formatting_lit (acc, fmting_lit)) rest
  1595.   | Formatting_gen (Open_tag (Format (fmt', _)), rest) ->
  1596. ‌    let k' kacc =
  1597.       make_printf k (Acc_formatting_gen (acc, Acc_open_tag kacc)) rest in
  1598.     make_printf k' End_of_acc fmt'
  1599.   | Formatting_gen (Open_box (Format (fmt', _)), rest) ->
  1600. ‌    let k' kacc =
  1601.       make_printf k (Acc_formatting_gen (acc, Acc_open_box kacc)) rest in
  1602.     make_printf k' End_of_acc fmt'

  1604.   | End_of_format ->
  1605.     k acc

  1607. (* Delay the error (Invalid_argument "Printf: bad conversion %_"). *)
  1608. (* Generate functions to take remaining arguments (after the "%_"). *)
  1609. ‌‌and make_ignored_param : type x y a b c d e f .
  1610.     ((b, c) acc -> f) -> (b, c) acc ->
  1611.     (a, b, c, d, y, x) ignored ->
  1612.     (x, b, c, y, e, f) fmt -> a =
  1613. fun k acc ign fmt -> match ign with
  1614.   | Ignored_char                    -> make_invalid_arg k acc fmt
  1615.   | Ignored_caml_char               -> make_invalid_arg k acc fmt
  1616.   | Ignored_string _                -> make_invalid_arg k acc fmt
  1617.   | Ignored_caml_string _           -> make_invalid_arg k acc fmt
  1618.   | Ignored_int (_, _)              -> make_invalid_arg k acc fmt
  1619.   | Ignored_int32 (_, _)            -> make_invalid_arg k acc fmt
  1620.   | Ignored_nativeint (_, _)        -> make_invalid_arg k acc fmt
  1621.   | Ignored_int64 (_, _)            -> make_invalid_arg k acc fmt
  1622.   | Ignored_float (_, _)            -> make_invalid_arg k acc fmt
  1623.   | Ignored_bool _                  -> make_invalid_arg k acc fmt
  1624.   | Ignored_format_arg _            -> make_invalid_arg k acc fmt
  1625.   | Ignored_format_subst (_, fmtty) -> make_from_fmtty k acc fmtty fmt
  1626.   | Ignored_reader                  -> assert false
  1627.   | Ignored_scan_char_set _         -> make_invalid_arg k acc fmt
  1628.   | Ignored_scan_get_counter _      -> make_invalid_arg k acc fmt
  1629.   | Ignored_scan_next_char          -> make_invalid_arg k acc fmt


  1632. (* Special case of printf "%_(". *)
  1633. ‌‌and make_from_fmtty : type x y a b c d e f .
  1634.     ((b, c) acc -> f) -> (b, c) acc ->
  1635.     (a, b, c, d, y, x) fmtty ->
  1636.     (x, b, c, y, e, f) fmt -> a =
  1637. fun k acc fmtty fmt -> match fmtty with
  1638.   | Char_ty rest            -> fun _ -> make_from_fmtty k acc rest fmt
  1639.   | String_ty rest          -> fun _ -> make_from_fmtty k acc rest fmt
  1640.   | Int_ty rest             -> fun _ -> make_from_fmtty k acc rest fmt
  1641.   | Int32_ty rest           -> fun _ -> make_from_fmtty k acc rest fmt
  1642.   | Nativeint_ty rest       -> fun _ -> make_from_fmtty k acc rest fmt
  1643.   | Int64_ty rest           -> fun _ -> make_from_fmtty k acc rest fmt
  1644.   | Float_ty rest           -> fun _ -> make_from_fmtty k acc rest fmt
  1645.   | Bool_ty rest            -> fun _ -> make_from_fmtty k acc rest fmt
  1646.   | Alpha_ty rest           -> fun _ _ -> make_from_fmtty k acc rest fmt
  1647.   | Theta_ty rest           -> fun _ -> make_from_fmtty k acc rest fmt
  1648.   | Any_ty rest             -> fun _ -> make_from_fmtty k acc rest fmt
  1649.   | Reader_ty _             -> assert false
  1650.   | Ignored_reader_ty _     -> assert false
  1651.   | Format_arg_ty (_, rest) -> fun _ -> make_from_fmtty k acc rest fmt
  1652.   | End_of_fmtty            -> make_invalid_arg k acc fmt
  1653.   | Format_subst_ty (ty1, ty2, rest) ->
  1654. ‌    let ty = trans (symm ty1) ty2 in
  1655.     fun _ -> make_from_fmtty k acc (concat_fmtty ty rest) fmt

  1657. (* Insert an Acc_invalid_arg in the accumulator and continue to generate
  1658.    closures to get the remaining arguments. *)
  1659. ‌‌and make_invalid_arg : type a b c d e f .
  1660.     ((b, c) acc -> f) -> (b, c) acc ->
  1661.     (a, b, c, d, e, f) fmt -> a =
  1662. fun k acc fmt ->
  1663.   make_printf k (Acc_invalid_arg (acc, "Printf: bad conversion %_")) fmt

  1665. (* Fix padding, take it as an extra integer argument if needed. *)
  1666. ‌‌and make_padding : type x z a b c d e f .
  1667.     ((b, c) acc -> f) -> (b, c) acc ->
  1668.     (a, b, c, d, e, f) fmt ->
  1669.     (x, z -> a) padding -> (z -> string) -> x =
  1670.   fun k acc fmt pad trans -> match pad with
  1671.   | No_padding ->
  1672.     fun x ->
  1673. ‌      let new_acc = Acc_data_string (acc, trans x) in
  1674.       make_printf k new_acc fmt
  1675.   | Lit_padding (padty, width) ->
  1676.     fun x ->
  1677. ‌      let new_acc = Acc_data_string (acc, fix_padding padty width (trans x)) in
  1678.       make_printf k new_acc fmt
  1679.   | Arg_padding padty ->
  1680.     fun w x ->
  1681. ‌      let new_acc = Acc_data_string (acc, fix_padding padty w (trans x)) in
  1682.       make_printf k new_acc fmt

  1684. (* Fix padding and precision for int, int32, nativeint or int64. *)
  1685. (* Take one or two extra integer arguments if needed. *)
  1686. ‌‌and make_int_padding_precision : type x y z a b c d e f .
  1687.     ((b, c) acc -> f) -> (b, c) acc ->
  1688.     (a, b, c, d, e, f) fmt ->
  1689.     (x, y) padding -> (y, z -> a) precision -> (int_conv -> z -> string) ->
  1690.     int_conv -> x =
  1691.   fun k acc fmt pad prec trans iconv -> match pad, prec with
  1692.   | No_padding, No_precision ->
  1693.     fun x ->
  1694. ‌      let str = trans iconv x in
  1695.       make_printf k (Acc_data_string (acc, str)) fmt
  1696.   | No_padding, Lit_precision p ->
  1697.     fun x ->
  1698. ‌      let str = fix_int_precision p (trans iconv x) in
  1699.       make_printf k (Acc_data_string (acc, str)) fmt
  1700.   | No_padding, Arg_precision ->
  1701.     fun p x ->
  1702. ‌      let str = fix_int_precision p (trans iconv x) in
  1703.       make_printf k (Acc_data_string (acc, str)) fmt
  1704.   | Lit_padding (padty, w), No_precision ->
  1705.     fun x ->
  1706. ‌      let str = fix_padding padty w (trans iconv x) in
  1707.       make_printf k (Acc_data_string (acc, str)) fmt
  1708.   | Lit_padding (padty, w), Lit_precision p ->
  1709.     fun x ->
  1710. ‌      let str = fix_padding padty w (fix_int_precision p (trans iconv x)) in
  1711.       make_printf k (Acc_data_string (acc, str)) fmt
  1712.   | Lit_padding (padty, w), Arg_precision ->
  1713.     fun p x ->
  1714. ‌      let str = fix_padding padty w (fix_int_precision p (trans iconv x)) in
  1715.       make_printf k (Acc_data_string (acc, str)) fmt
  1716.   | Arg_padding padty, No_precision ->
  1717.     fun w x ->
  1718. ‌      let str = fix_padding padty w (trans iconv x) in
  1719.       make_printf k (Acc_data_string (acc, str)) fmt
  1720.   | Arg_padding padty, Lit_precision p ->
  1721.     fun w x ->
  1722. ‌      let str = fix_padding padty w (fix_int_precision p (trans iconv x)) in
  1723.       make_printf k (Acc_data_string (acc, str)) fmt
  1724.   | Arg_padding padty, Arg_precision ->
  1725.     fun w p x ->
  1726. ‌      let str = fix_padding padty w (fix_int_precision p (trans iconv x)) in
  1727.       make_printf k (Acc_data_string (acc, str)) fmt

  1729. (* Convert a float, fix padding and precision if needed. *)
  1730. (* Take the float argument and one or two extra integer arguments if needed. *)
  1731. ‌‌and make_float_padding_precision : type x y a b c d e f .
  1732.     ((b, c) acc -> f) -> (b, c) acc ->
  1733.     (a, b, c, d, e, f) fmt ->
  1734.     (x, y) padding -> (y, float -> a) precision -> float_conv -> x =
  1735.   fun k acc fmt pad prec fconv -> match pad, prec with
  1736.   | No_padding, No_precision ->
  1737.     fun x ->
  1738. ‌      let str = convert_float fconv (default_float_precision fconv) x in
  1739.       make_printf k (Acc_data_string (acc, str)) fmt
  1740.   | No_padding, Lit_precision p ->
  1741.     fun x ->
  1742. ‌      let str = convert_float fconv p x in
  1743.       make_printf k (Acc_data_string (acc, str)) fmt
  1744.   | No_padding, Arg_precision ->
  1745.     fun p x ->
  1746. ‌      let str = convert_float fconv p x in
  1747.       make_printf k (Acc_data_string (acc, str)) fmt
  1748.   | Lit_padding (padty, w), No_precision ->
  1749.     fun x ->
  1750. ‌      let str = convert_float fconv (default_float_precision fconv) x in
  1751. ‌      let str' = fix_padding padty w str in
  1752.       make_printf k (Acc_data_string (acc, str')) fmt
  1753.   | Lit_padding (padty, w), Lit_precision p ->
  1754.     fun x ->
  1755. ‌      let str = fix_padding padty w (convert_float fconv p x) in
  1756.       make_printf k (Acc_data_string (acc, str)) fmt
  1757.   | Lit_padding (padty, w), Arg_precision ->
  1758.     fun p x ->
  1759. ‌      let str = fix_padding padty w (convert_float fconv p x) in
  1760.       make_printf k (Acc_data_string (acc, str)) fmt
  1761.   | Arg_padding padty, No_precision ->
  1762.     fun w x ->
  1763. ‌      let str = convert_float fconv (default_float_precision fconv) x in
  1764. ‌      let str' = fix_padding padty w str in
  1765.       make_printf k (Acc_data_string (acc, str')) fmt
  1766.   | Arg_padding padty, Lit_precision p ->
  1767.     fun w x ->
  1768. ‌      let str = fix_padding padty w (convert_float fconv p x) in
  1769.       make_printf k (Acc_data_string (acc, str)) fmt
  1770.   | Arg_padding padty, Arg_precision ->
  1771.     fun w p x ->
  1772. ‌      let str = fix_padding padty w (convert_float fconv p x) in
  1773.       make_printf k (Acc_data_string (acc, str)) fmt
  1774. ‌‌and make_custom : type x y a b c d e f .
  1775.   ((b, c) acc -> f) -> (b, c) acc ->
  1776.   (a, b, c, d, e, f) fmt ->
  1777.   (a, x, y) custom_arity -> x -> y =
  1778.   fun k acc rest arity f -> match arity with
  1779.   | Custom_zero -> make_printf k (Acc_data_string (acc, f)) rest
  1780.   | Custom_succ arity ->
  1781.     fun x ->
  1782.       make_custom k acc rest arity (f x)

  1784. ‌let const x _ = x

  1786. ‌‌let rec make_iprintf : type a b c d e f state.
  1787.   (state -> f) -> state -> (a, b, c, d, e, f) fmt -> a =
  1788.   fun k o fmt -> match fmt with
  1789.     | Char rest ->
  1790.         const (make_iprintf k o rest)
  1791.     | Caml_char rest ->
  1792.         const (make_iprintf k o rest)
  1793.     | String (No_padding, rest) ->
  1794.         const (make_iprintf k o rest)
  1795.     | String (Lit_padding _, rest) ->
  1796.         const (make_iprintf k o rest)
  1797.     | String (Arg_padding _, rest) ->
  1798.         const (const (make_iprintf k o rest))
  1799.     | Caml_string (No_padding, rest) ->
  1800.         const (make_iprintf k o rest)
  1801.     | Caml_string (Lit_padding _, rest) ->
  1802.         const (make_iprintf k o rest)
  1803.     | Caml_string (Arg_padding _, rest) ->
  1804.         const (const (make_iprintf k o rest))
  1805.     | Int (_, pad, prec, rest) ->
  1806.         fn_of_padding_precision k o rest pad prec
  1807.     | Int32 (_, pad, prec, rest) ->
