  1808.         fn_of_padding_precision k o rest pad prec
  1809.     | Nativeint (_, pad, prec, rest) ->
  1810.         fn_of_padding_precision k o rest pad prec
  1811.     | Int64 (_, pad, prec, rest) ->
  1812.         fn_of_padding_precision k o rest pad prec
  1813.     | Float (_, pad, prec, rest) ->
  1814.         fn_of_padding_precision k o rest pad prec
  1815.     | Bool (No_padding, rest) ->
  1816.         const (make_iprintf k o rest)
  1817.     | Bool (Lit_padding _, rest) ->
  1818.         const (make_iprintf k o rest)
  1819.     | Bool (Arg_padding _, rest) ->
  1820.         const (const (make_iprintf k o rest))
  1821.     | Alpha rest ->
  1822.         const (const (make_iprintf k o rest))
  1823.     | Theta rest ->
  1824.         const (make_iprintf k o rest)
  1825.     | Custom (arity, _, rest) ->
  1826.         fn_of_custom_arity k o rest arity
  1827.     | Reader _ ->
  1828.         (* This case is impossible, by typing of formats.  See the
  1829.            note in the corresponding case for make_printf. *)
  1830.         assert false
  1831.     | Flush rest ->
  1832.         make_iprintf k o rest
  1833.     | String_literal (_, rest) ->
  1834.         make_iprintf k o rest
  1835.     | Char_literal (_, rest) ->
  1836.         make_iprintf k o rest
  1837.     | Format_arg (_, _, rest) ->
  1838.         const (make_iprintf k o rest)
  1839.     | Format_subst (_, fmtty, rest) ->
  1840.         fun (Format (fmt, _)) ->
  1841.           make_iprintf k o
  1842.             (concat_fmt (recast fmt fmtty) rest)
  1843.     | Scan_char_set (_, _, rest) ->
  1844.         const (make_iprintf k o rest)
  1845.     | Scan_get_counter (_, rest) ->
  1846.         const (make_iprintf k o rest)
  1847.     | Scan_next_char rest ->
  1848.         const (make_iprintf k o rest)
  1849.     | Ignored_param (ign, rest) ->
  1850.         make_ignored_param (fun _ -> k o) (End_of_acc) ign rest
  1851.     | Formatting_lit (_, rest) ->
  1852.         make_iprintf k o rest
  1853.     | Formatting_gen (Open_tag (Format (fmt', _)), rest) ->
  1854.         make_iprintf (fun koc -> make_iprintf k koc rest) o fmt'
  1855.     | Formatting_gen (Open_box (Format (fmt', _)), rest) ->
  1856.         make_iprintf (fun koc -> make_iprintf k koc rest) o fmt'
  1857.     | End_of_format ->
  1858.         k o
  1859. ‌and fn_of_padding_precision :
  1860. ‌  type x y z a b c d e f state.
  1861.   (state -> f) -> state -> (a, b, c, d, e, f) fmt ->
  1862.   (x, y) padding -> (y, z -> a) precision -> x =
  1863.   fun k o fmt pad prec -> match pad, prec with
  1864.     | No_padding   , No_precision    ->
  1865.         const (make_iprintf k o fmt)
  1866.     | No_padding   , Lit_precision _ ->
  1867.         const (make_iprintf k o fmt)
  1868.     | No_padding   , Arg_precision   ->
  1869.         const (const (make_iprintf k o fmt))
  1870.     | Lit_padding _, No_precision    ->
  1871.         const (make_iprintf k o fmt)
  1872.     | Lit_padding _, Lit_precision _ ->
  1873.         const (make_iprintf k o fmt)
  1874.     | Lit_padding _, Arg_precision   ->
  1875.         const (const (make_iprintf k o fmt))
  1876.     | Arg_padding _, No_precision    ->
  1877.         const (const (make_iprintf k o fmt))
  1878.     | Arg_padding _, Lit_precision _ ->
  1879.         const (const (make_iprintf k o fmt))
  1880.     | Arg_padding _, Arg_precision   ->
  1881.         const (const (const (make_iprintf k o fmt)))
  1882. ‌‌and fn_of_custom_arity : type x y a b c d e f state.
  1883.   (state -> f) ->
  1884.   state -> (a, b, c, d, e, f) fmt -> (a, x, y) custom_arity -> y =
  1885.   fun k o fmt -> function
  1886.     | Custom_zero ->
  1887.         make_iprintf k o fmt
  1888.     | Custom_succ arity ->
  1889.         const (fn_of_custom_arity k o fmt arity)

  1891. (******************************************************************************)
  1892.                           (* Continuations for make_printf *)

  1894. (* Recursively output an "accumulator" containing a reversed list of
  1895.    printing entities (string, char, flus, ...) in an output_stream. *)
  1896. (* Used as a continuation of make_printf. *)
  1897. ‌let rec output_acc o acc = match acc with
  1898.   | Acc_formatting_lit (p, fmting_lit) ->
  1899.     let s = string_of_formatting_lit fmting_lit in
  1900.     output_acc o p; output_string o s;
  1901.   | Acc_formatting_gen (p, Acc_open_tag acc') ->
  1902.     output_acc o p; output_string o "@{"; output_acc o acc';
  1903.   | Acc_formatting_gen (p, Acc_open_box acc') ->
  1904.     output_acc o p; output_string o "@["; output_acc o acc';
  1905.   | Acc_string_literal (p, s)
  1906.   | Acc_data_string (p, s)   -> output_acc o p; output_string o s
  1907.   | Acc_char_literal (p, c)
  1908.   | Acc_data_char (p, c)     -> output_acc o p; output_char o c
  1909.   | Acc_delay (p, f)         -> output_acc o p; f o
  1910.   | Acc_flush p              -> output_acc o p; flush o
  1911.   | Acc_invalid_arg (p, msg) -> output_acc o p; invalid_arg msg;
  1912.   | End_of_acc               -> ()

  1914. (* Recursively output an "accumulator" containing a reversed list of
  1915.    printing entities (string, char, flus, ...) in a buffer. *)
  1916. (* Used as a continuation of make_printf. *)
  1917. ‌let rec bufput_acc b acc = match acc with
  1918.   | Acc_formatting_lit (p, fmting_lit) ->
  1919.     let s = string_of_formatting_lit fmting_lit in
  1920.     bufput_acc b p; Buffer.add_string b s;
  1921.   | Acc_formatting_gen (p, Acc_open_tag acc') ->
  1922.     bufput_acc b p; Buffer.add_string b "@{"; bufput_acc b acc';
  1923.   | Acc_formatting_gen (p, Acc_open_box acc') ->
  1924.     bufput_acc b p; Buffer.add_string b "@["; bufput_acc b acc';
  1925.   | Acc_string_literal (p, s)
  1926.   | Acc_data_string (p, s)   -> bufput_acc b p; Buffer.add_string b s
  1927.   | Acc_char_literal (p, c)
  1928.   | Acc_data_char (p, c)     -> bufput_acc b p; Buffer.add_char b c
  1929.   | Acc_delay (p, f)         -> bufput_acc b p; f b
  1930.   | Acc_flush p              -> bufput_acc b p;
  1931.   | Acc_invalid_arg (p, msg) -> bufput_acc b p; invalid_arg msg;
  1932.   | End_of_acc               -> ()

  1934. (* Recursively output an "accumulator" containing a reversed list of
  1935.    printing entities (string, char, flus, ...) in a buffer. *)
  1936. (* Differ from bufput_acc by the interpretation of %a and %t. *)
  1937. (* Used as a continuation of make_printf. *)
  1938. ‌let rec strput_acc b acc = match acc with
  1939.   | Acc_formatting_lit (p, fmting_lit) ->
  1940.     let s = string_of_formatting_lit fmting_lit in
  1941.     strput_acc b p; Buffer.add_string b s;
  1942.   | Acc_formatting_gen (p, Acc_open_tag acc') ->
  1943.     strput_acc b p; Buffer.add_string b "@{"; strput_acc b acc';
  1944.   | Acc_formatting_gen (p, Acc_open_box acc') ->
  1945.     strput_acc b p; Buffer.add_string b "@["; strput_acc b acc';
  1946.   | Acc_string_literal (p, s)
  1947.   | Acc_data_string (p, s)   -> strput_acc b p; Buffer.add_string b s
  1948.   | Acc_char_literal (p, c)
  1949.   | Acc_data_char (p, c)     -> strput_acc b p; Buffer.add_char b c
  1950.   | Acc_delay (p, f)         -> strput_acc b p; Buffer.add_string b (f ())
  1951.   | Acc_flush p              -> strput_acc b p;
  1952.   | Acc_invalid_arg (p, msg) -> strput_acc b p; invalid_arg msg;
  1953.   | End_of_acc               -> ()

  1955. (******************************************************************************)
  1956.                           (* Error management *)

  1958. (* Raise [Failure] with a pretty-printed error message. *)
  1959. ‌let failwith_message (Format (fmt, _)) =
  1960.   let buf = Buffer.create 256 in
  1961.   let k acc = strput_acc buf acc; failwith (Buffer.contents buf) in
  1962.   make_printf k End_of_acc fmt

  1964. (******************************************************************************)
  1965.                             (* Formatting tools *)

  1967. (* Convert a string to an open block description (indent, block_type) *)
  1968. ‌let open_box_of_string str =
  1969.   if str = "" then (0, Pp_box) else
  1970.     let len = String.length str in
  1971.     let invalid_box () = failwith_message "invalid box description %S" str in
  1972.     let rec parse_spaces i =
  1973.       if i = len then i else
  1974.         match str.[i] with
  1975.         | ' ' | '\t' -> parse_spaces (i + 1)
  1976.         | _ -> i
  1977.     and parse_lword i j =
  1978.       if j = len then j else
  1979.         match str.[j] with
  1980.         | 'a' .. 'z' -> parse_lword i (j + 1)
  1981.         | _ -> j
  1982.     and parse_int i j =
  1983.       if j = len then j else
  1984.         match str.[j] with
  1985.         | '0' .. '9' | '-' -> parse_int i (j + 1)
  1986.         | _ -> j in
  1987. ‌    let wstart = parse_spaces 0 in
  1988. ‌    let wend = parse_lword wstart wstart in
  1989. ‌    let box_name = String.sub str wstart (wend - wstart) in
  1990. ‌    let nstart = parse_spaces wend in
  1991. ‌    let nend = parse_int nstart nstart in
  1992. ‌    let indent =
  1993.       if nstart = nend then 0 else
  1994.         try int_of_string (String.sub str nstart (nend - nstart))
  1995.         with Failure _ -> invalid_box () in
  1996. ‌    let exp_end = parse_spaces nend in
  1997.     if exp_end <> len then invalid_box ();
  1998. ‌    let box_type = match box_name with
  1999.       | "" | "b" -> Pp_box
  2000.       | "h"      -> Pp_hbox
  2001.       | "v"      -> Pp_vbox
  2002.       | "hv"     -> Pp_hvbox
  2003.       | "hov"    -> Pp_hovbox
  2004.       | _        -> invalid_box () in
  2005.     (indent, box_type)

  2007. (******************************************************************************)
  2008.                             (* Parsing tools *)

  2010. (* Create a padding_fmt_ebb from a padding and a format. *)
  2011. (* Copy the padding to disjoin the type parameters of argument and result. *)
  2012. ‌‌let make_padding_fmt_ebb : type x y .
  2013.     (x, y) padding -> (_, _, _, _, _, _) fmt ->
  2014.       (_, _, _, _, _) padding_fmt_ebb =
  2015. fun pad fmt -> match pad with
  2016.   | No_padding         -> Padding_fmt_EBB (No_padding, fmt)
  2017.   | Lit_padding (s, w) -> Padding_fmt_EBB (Lit_padding (s, w), fmt)
  2018.   | Arg_padding s      -> Padding_fmt_EBB (Arg_padding s, fmt)

  2020. (* Create a precision_fmt_ebb from a precision and a format. *)
  2021. (* Copy the precision to disjoin the type parameters of argument and result. *)
  2022. ‌‌let make_precision_fmt_ebb : type x y .
  2023.     (x, y) precision -> (_, _, _, _, _, _) fmt ->
  2024.       (_, _, _, _, _) precision_fmt_ebb =
  2025. fun prec fmt -> match prec with
  2026.   | No_precision    -> Precision_fmt_EBB (No_precision, fmt)
  2027.   | Lit_precision p -> Precision_fmt_EBB (Lit_precision p, fmt)
  2028.   | Arg_precision   -> Precision_fmt_EBB (Arg_precision, fmt)

  2030. (* Create a padprec_fmt_ebb from a padding, a precision and a format. *)
  2031. (* Copy the padding and the precision to disjoin type parameters of arguments
  2032.    and result. *)
  2033. ‌‌let make_padprec_fmt_ebb : type x y z t .
  2034.     (x, y) padding -> (z, t) precision ->
  2035.     (_, _, _, _, _, _) fmt ->
  2036.     (_, _, _, _, _) padprec_fmt_ebb =
  2037. fun pad prec fmt ->
  2038. ‌  let Precision_fmt_EBB (prec, fmt') = make_precision_fmt_ebb prec fmt in
  2039.   match pad with
  2040.   | No_padding         -> Padprec_fmt_EBB (No_padding, prec, fmt')
  2041.   | Lit_padding (s, w) -> Padprec_fmt_EBB (Lit_padding (s, w), prec, fmt')
  2042.   | Arg_padding s      -> Padprec_fmt_EBB (Arg_padding s, prec, fmt')

  2044. (******************************************************************************)
  2045.                              (* Format parsing *)

  2047. (* Parse a string representing a format and create a fmt_ebb. *)
  2048. (* Raise [Failure] in case of invalid format. *)
  2049. ‌let fmt_ebb_of_string ?legacy_behavior str =
  2050.   (* Parameters naming convention:                                    *)
  2051.   (*   - lit_start: start of the literal sequence.                    *)
  2052.   (*   - str_ind: current index in the string.                        *)
  2053.   (*   - end_ind: end of the current (sub-)format.                    *)
  2054.   (*   - pct_ind: index of the '%' in the current micro-format.       *)
  2055.   (*   - zero:  is the '0' flag defined in the current micro-format.  *)
  2056.   (*   - minus: is the '-' flag defined in the current micro-format.  *)
  2057.   (*   - plus:  is the '+' flag defined in the current micro-format.  *)
  2058.   (*   - hash:  is the '#' flag defined in the current micro-format.  *)
  2059.   (*   - space: is the ' ' flag defined in the current micro-format.  *)
  2060.   (*   - ign:   is the '_' flag defined in the current micro-format.  *)
  2061.   (*   - pad: padding of the current micro-format.                    *)
  2062.   (*   - prec: precision of the current micro-format.                 *)
  2063.   (*   - symb: char representing the conversion ('c', 's', 'd', ...). *)
  2064.   (*   - char_set: set of characters as bitmap (see scanf %[...]).    *)

  2066.   let legacy_behavior = match legacy_behavior with
  2067.     | Some flag -> flag
  2068.     | None -> true
  2069.   (*  When this flag is enabled, the format parser tries to behave as
  2070.       the <4.02 implementations, in particular it ignores most benine
  2071.       nonsensical format. When the flag is disabled, it will reject any
  2072.       format that is not accepted by the specification.

  2074.       A typical example would be "%+ d": specifying both '+' (if the
  2075.       number is positive, pad with a '+' to get the same width as
  2076.       negative numbers) and ' ' (if the number is positive, pad with
  2077.       a space) does not make sense, but the legacy (< 4.02)
  2078.       implementation was happy to just ignore the space.
  2079.   *)
  2080.   in

  2082.   (* Raise [Failure] with a friendly error message. *)
  2083.   let invalid_format_message str_ind msg =
  2084.     failwith_message
  2085.       "invalid format %S: at character number %d, %s"
  2086.       str str_ind msg
  2087.   in

  2089.   (* Used when the end of the format (or the current sub-format) was encountered
  2090.       unexpectedly. *)
  2091.   let unexpected_end_of_format end_ind =
  2092.     invalid_format_message end_ind
  2093.       "unexpected end of format"
  2094.   in

  2096.   (* Used for %0c: no other widths are implemented *)
  2097.   let invalid_nonnull_char_width str_ind =
  2098.     invalid_format_message str_ind
  2099.       "non-zero widths are unsupported for %c conversions"
  2100.   in
  2101.   (* Raise [Failure] with a friendly error message about an option dependency
  2102.      problem. *)
  2103.   let invalid_format_without str_ind c s =
  2104.     failwith_message
  2105.       "invalid format %S: at character number %d, '%c' without %s"
  2106.       str str_ind c s
  2107.   in

  2109.   (* Raise [Failure] with a friendly error message about an unexpected
  2110.      character. *)
  2111.   let expected_character str_ind expected read =
  2112.     failwith_message
  2113.      "invalid format %S: at character number %d, %s expected, read %C"
  2114.       str str_ind expected read
  2115.   in

  2117.   (* Parse the string from beg_ind (included) to end_ind (excluded). *)
  2118. ‌  let rec parse : type e f . int -> int -> (_, _, e, f) fmt_ebb =
  2119.   fun beg_ind end_ind -> parse_literal beg_ind beg_ind end_ind

  2121.   (* Read literal characters up to '%' or '@' special characters. *)
  2122. ‌‌  and parse_literal : type e f . int -> int -> int -> (_, _, e, f) fmt_ebb =
  2123.   fun lit_start str_ind end_ind ->
  2124.     if str_ind = end_ind then add_literal lit_start str_ind End_of_format else
  2125.       match str.[str_ind] with
  2126.       | '%' ->
  2127.         let Fmt_EBB fmt_rest = parse_format str_ind end_ind in
  2128.         add_literal lit_start str_ind fmt_rest
  2129.       | '@' ->
  2130. ‌        let Fmt_EBB fmt_rest = parse_after_at (str_ind + 1) end_ind in
  2131.         add_literal lit_start str_ind fmt_rest
  2132.       | _ ->
  2133.         parse_literal lit_start (str_ind + 1) end_ind

  2135.   (* Parse a format after '%' *)
  2136. ‌‌  and parse_format : type e f . int -> int -> (_, _, e, f) fmt_ebb =
  2137.   fun pct_ind end_ind -> parse_ign pct_ind (pct_ind + 1) end_ind

  2139. ‌‌  and parse_ign : type e f . int -> int -> int -> (_, _, e, f) fmt_ebb =
  2140.   fun pct_ind str_ind end_ind ->
  2141.     if str_ind = end_ind then unexpected_end_of_format end_ind;
  2142.     match str.[str_ind] with
  2143.       | '_' -> parse_flags pct_ind (str_ind+1) end_ind true
  2144.       | _ -> parse_flags pct_ind str_ind end_ind false

  2146. ‌‌  and parse_flags : type e f . int -> int -> int -> bool -> (_, _, e, f) fmt_ebb
  2147.   =
  2148.   fun pct_ind str_ind end_ind ign ->
  2149. ‌    let zero = ref false and minus = ref false
  2150.     and plus = ref false and space = ref false
  2151.     and hash = ref false in
  2152.     let set_flag str_ind flag =
  2153.       (* in legacy mode, duplicate flags are accepted *)
  2154.       if !flag && not legacy_behavior then
  2155.         failwith_message
  2156.           "invalid format %S: at character number %d, duplicate flag %C"
  2157.           str str_ind str.[str_ind];
  2158.       flag := true;
  2159.     in
  2160. ‌    let rec read_flags str_ind =
  2161.       if str_ind = end_ind then unexpected_end_of_format end_ind;
  2162.       begin match str.[str_ind] with
  2163.       | '0' -> set_flag str_ind zero;  read_flags (str_ind + 1)
  2164.       | '-' -> set_flag str_ind minus; read_flags (str_ind + 1)
  2165.       | '+' -> set_flag str_ind plus;  read_flags (str_ind + 1)
  2166.       | '#' -> set_flag str_ind hash; read_flags (str_ind + 1)
  2167.       | ' ' -> set_flag str_ind space; read_flags (str_ind + 1)
  2168.       | _ ->
  2169.         parse_padding pct_ind str_ind end_ind
  2170.           !zero !minus !plus !hash !space ign
  2171.       end
  2172.     in
  2173.     read_flags str_ind

  2175.   (* Try to read a digital or a '*' padding. *)
  2176. ‌‌  and parse_padding : type e f .
  2177.       int -> int -> int -> bool -> bool -> bool -> bool -> bool -> bool ->
  2178.         (_, _, e, f) fmt_ebb =
  2179.   fun pct_ind str_ind end_ind zero minus plus hash space ign ->
  2180.     if str_ind = end_ind then unexpected_end_of_format end_ind;
  2181. ‌    let padty = match zero, minus with
  2182.       | false, false -> Right
  2183.       | false, true  -> Left
  2184.       |  true, false -> Zeros
  2185.       |  true, true  ->
  2186.         if legacy_behavior then Left
  2187.         else incompatible_flag pct_ind str_ind '-' "0" in
  2188.     match str.[str_ind] with
  2189.     | '0' .. '9' ->
  2190. ‌      let new_ind, width = parse_positive str_ind end_ind 0 in
  2191.       parse_after_padding pct_ind new_ind end_ind minus plus hash space ign
  2192.         (Lit_padding (padty, width))
  2193.     | '*' ->
  2194.       parse_after_padding pct_ind (str_ind + 1) end_ind minus plus hash space
  2195.         ign (Arg_padding padty)
  2196.     | _ ->
  2197.       begin match padty with
  2198.       | Left  ->
  2199.         if not legacy_behavior then
  2200.           invalid_format_without (str_ind - 1) '-' "padding";
  2201.         parse_after_padding pct_ind str_ind end_ind minus plus hash space ign
  2202.           No_padding
  2203.       | Zeros ->
  2204.          (* a '0' padding indication not followed by anything should
  2205.            be interpreted as a Right padding of width 0. This is used
  2206.            by scanning conversions %0s and %0c *)
  2207.         parse_after_padding pct_ind str_ind end_ind minus plus hash space ign
  2208.           (Lit_padding (Right, 0))
  2209.       | Right ->
  2210.         parse_after_padding pct_ind str_ind end_ind minus plus hash space ign
  2211.           No_padding
  2212.       end

  2214.   (* Is precision defined? *)
  2215. ‌‌  and parse_after_padding : type x e f .
  2216.       int -> int -> int -> bool -> bool -> bool -> bool -> bool ->
  2217.         (x, _) padding -> (_, _, e, f) fmt_ebb =
  2218.   fun pct_ind str_ind end_ind minus plus hash space ign pad ->
  2219.     if str_ind = end_ind then unexpected_end_of_format end_ind;
  2220.     match str.[str_ind] with
  2221.     | '.' ->
  2222.       parse_precision pct_ind (str_ind + 1) end_ind minus plus hash space ign
  2223.         pad
  2224.     | symb ->
  2225.       parse_conversion pct_ind (str_ind + 1) end_ind plus hash space ign pad
  2226.         No_precision pad symb

  2228.   (* Read the digital or '*' precision. *)
  2229. ‌‌  and parse_precision : type x e f .
  2230.       int -> int -> int -> bool -> bool -> bool -> bool -> bool ->
  2231.         (x, _) padding -> (_, _, e, f) fmt_ebb =
  2232.   fun pct_ind str_ind end_ind minus plus hash space ign pad ->
  2233.     if str_ind = end_ind then unexpected_end_of_format end_ind;
  2234. ‌    let parse_literal minus str_ind =
  2235.       let new_ind, prec = parse_positive str_ind end_ind 0 in
  2236.       parse_after_precision pct_ind new_ind end_ind minus plus hash space ign
  2237.         pad (Lit_precision prec) in
  2238.     match str.[str_ind] with
  2239.     | '0' .. '9' -> parse_literal minus str_ind
  2240.     | ('+' | '-') as symb when legacy_behavior ->
  2241.       (* Legacy mode would accept and ignore '+' or '-' before the
  2242.          integer describing the desired precision; note that this
  2243.          cannot happen for padding width, as '+' and '-' already have
  2244.          a semantics there.

  2246.          That said, the idea (supported by this tweak) that width and
  2247.          precision literals are "integer literals" in the OCaml sense is
  2248.          still blatantly wrong, as 123_456 or 0xFF are rejected. *)
  2249.       parse_literal (minus || symb = '-') (str_ind + 1)
  2250.     | '*' ->
  2251.       parse_after_precision pct_ind (str_ind + 1) end_ind minus plus hash space
  2252.         ign pad Arg_precision
  2253.     | _ ->
  2254.       if legacy_behavior then
  2255.         (* note that legacy implementation did not ignore '.' without
  2256.            a number (as it does for padding indications), but
  2257.            interprets it as '.0' *)
  2258.         parse_after_precision pct_ind str_ind end_ind minus plus hash space ign
  2259.           pad (Lit_precision 0)
  2260.       else
  2261.         invalid_format_without (str_ind - 1) '.' "precision"

  2263.   (* Try to read the conversion. *)
  2264. ‌‌  and parse_after_precision : type x y z t e f .
  2265.       int -> int -> int -> bool -> bool -> bool -> bool -> bool ->
  2266.         (x, y) padding -> (z, t) precision -> (_, _, e, f) fmt_ebb =
  2267.   fun pct_ind str_ind end_ind minus plus hash space ign pad prec ->
  2268.     if str_ind = end_ind then unexpected_end_of_format end_ind;
  2269. ‌    let parse_conv (type u) (type v) (padprec : (u, v) padding) =
  2270.       parse_conversion pct_ind (str_ind + 1) end_ind plus hash space ign pad
  2271.         prec padprec str.[str_ind] in
  2272.     (* in legacy mode, some formats (%s and %S) accept a weird mix of
  2273.        padding and precision, which is merged as a single padding
  2274.        information. For example, in %.10s the precision is implicitly
  2275.        understood as padding %10s, but the left-padding component may
  2276.        be specified either as a left padding or a negative precision:
  2277.        %-.3s and %.-3s are equivalent to %-3s *)
  2278.     match pad with
  2279.     | No_padding -> (
  2280.       match minus, prec with
  2281.         | _, No_precision -> parse_conv No_padding
  2282.         | false, Lit_precision n -> parse_conv (Lit_padding (Right, n))
  2283.         | true, Lit_precision n -> parse_conv (Lit_padding (Left, n))
  2284.         | false, Arg_precision -> parse_conv (Arg_padding Right)
  2285.         | true, Arg_precision -> parse_conv (Arg_padding Left)
  2286.     )
  2287.     | pad -> parse_conv pad

  2289.   (* Case analysis on conversion. *)
  2290. ‌‌  and parse_conversion : type x y z t u v e f .
  2291.       int -> int -> int -> bool -> bool -> bool -> bool -> (x, y) padding ->
  2292.         (z, t) precision -> (u, v) padding -> char -> (_, _, e, f) fmt_ebb =
  2293.   fun pct_ind str_ind end_ind plus hash space ign pad prec padprec symb ->
  2294.     (* Flags used to check option usages/compatibilities. *)
  2295. ‌    let plus_used  = ref false and hash_used = ref false
  2296.     and space_used = ref false and ign_used   = ref false
  2297.     and pad_used   = ref false and prec_used  = ref false in

  2299.     (* Access to options, update flags. *)
  2300.     let get_plus    () = plus_used  := true; plus
  2301.     and get_hash   () = hash_used := true; hash
  2302.     and get_space   () = space_used := true; space
  2303.     and get_ign     () = ign_used   := true; ign
  2304.     and get_pad     () = pad_used   := true; pad
  2305.     and get_prec    () = prec_used  := true; prec
  2306.     and get_padprec () = pad_used   := true; padprec in

  2308.     let get_int_pad () : (x,y) padding =
  2309.       (* %5.3d is accepted and meaningful: pad to length 5 with
  2310.          spaces, but first pad with zeros upto length 3 (0-padding
  2311.          is the interpretation of "precision" for integer formats).

  2313.          %05.3d is redundant: pad to length 5 *with zeros*, but
  2314.          first pad with zeros... To add insult to the injury, the
  2315.          legacy implementation ignores the 0-padding indication and
  2316.          does the 5 padding with spaces instead. We reuse this
  2317.          interpretation for compatibility, but statically reject this
  2318.          format when the legacy mode is disabled, to protect strict
  2319.          users from this corner case. *)
  2320.        match get_pad (), get_prec () with
  2321.          | pad, No_precision -> pad
  2322.          | No_padding, _     -> No_padding
  2323.          | Lit_padding (Zeros, n), _ ->
  2324.            if legacy_behavior then Lit_padding (Right, n)
  2325.            else incompatible_flag pct_ind str_ind '0' "precision"
  2326.          | Arg_padding Zeros, _ ->
  2327.            if legacy_behavior then Arg_padding Right
  2328.            else incompatible_flag pct_ind str_ind '0' "precision"
  2329.          | Lit_padding _ as pad, _ -> pad
  2330.          | Arg_padding _ as pad, _ -> pad in

  2332.     (* Check that padty <> Zeros. *)
  2333. ‌    let check_no_0 symb (type a b) (pad : (a, b) padding) : (a,b) padding =
  2334.       match pad with
  2335.       | No_padding -> pad
  2336.       | Lit_padding ((Left | Right), _) -> pad
  2337.       | Arg_padding (Left | Right) -> pad
  2338.       | Lit_padding (Zeros, width) ->
  2339.         if legacy_behavior then Lit_padding (Right, width)
  2340.         else incompatible_flag pct_ind str_ind symb "0"
  2341.       | Arg_padding Zeros ->
  2342.         if legacy_behavior then Arg_padding Right
  2343.         else incompatible_flag pct_ind str_ind symb "0"
  2344.     in

  2346.     (* Get padding as a pad_option (see "%_", "%{", "%(" and "%[").
  2347.        (no need for legacy mode tweaking, those were rejected by the
  2348.        legacy parser as well) *)
  2349. ‌    let opt_of_pad c (type a) (type b) (pad : (a, b) padding) = match pad with
  2350.       | No_padding -> None
  2351.       | Lit_padding (Right, width) -> Some width
  2352.       | Lit_padding (Zeros, width) ->
  2353.         if legacy_behavior then Some width
  2354.         else incompatible_flag pct_ind str_ind c "'0'"
  2355.       | Lit_padding (Left, width) ->
  2356.         if legacy_behavior then Some width
  2357.         else incompatible_flag pct_ind str_ind c "'-'"
  2358.       | Arg_padding _ -> incompatible_flag pct_ind str_ind c "'*'"
  2359.     in
  2360. ‌    let get_pad_opt c = opt_of_pad c (get_pad ()) in
  2361. ‌    let get_padprec_opt c = opt_of_pad c (get_padprec ()) in

  2363.     (* Get precision as a prec_option (see "%_f").
  2364.        (no need for legacy mode tweaking, those were rejected by the
  2365.        legacy parser as well) *)
  2366. ‌    let get_prec_opt () = match get_prec () with
  2367.       | No_precision       -> None
  2368.       | Lit_precision ndec -> Some ndec
  2369.       | Arg_precision      -> incompatible_flag pct_ind str_ind '_' "'*'"
  2370.     in

  2372. ‌    let fmt_result = match symb with
  2373.     | ',' ->
  2374.       parse str_ind end_ind
  2375.     | 'c' ->
  2376.       let char_format fmt_rest = (* %c *)
  2377.         if get_ign ()
  2378.         then Fmt_EBB (Ignored_param (Ignored_char, fmt_rest))
  2379.         else Fmt_EBB (Char fmt_rest)
  2380.       in
  2381. ‌      let scan_format fmt_rest = (* %0c *)

  2384.         else Fmt_EBB (Scan_next_char fmt_rest)
  2385.       in
  2386. ‌      let Fmt_EBB fmt_rest = parse str_ind end_ind in

  2388.         | None -> char_format fmt_rest
  2389.         | Some 0 -> scan_format fmt_rest
  2390.         | Some _n ->
  2391.            if not legacy_behavior
  2392.            then invalid_nonnull_char_width str_ind

  2394.       end
  2395.     | 'C' ->
  2396. ‌      let Fmt_EBB fmt_rest = parse str_ind end_ind in
  2397.       if get_ign () then Fmt_EBB (Ignored_param (Ignored_caml_char,fmt_rest))

  2399.     | 's' ->
  2400. ‌      let pad = check_no_0 symb (get_padprec ()) in
  2401. ‌      let Fmt_EBB fmt_rest = parse str_ind end_ind in
  2402.       if get_ign () then
  2403. ‌        let ignored = Ignored_string (get_padprec_opt '_') in
  2404.         Fmt_EBB (Ignored_param (ignored, fmt_rest))
  2405.       else
  2406. ‌        let Padding_fmt_EBB (pad', fmt_rest') =
  2407.           make_padding_fmt_ebb pad fmt_rest in
  2408.         Fmt_EBB (String (pad', fmt_rest'))
  2409.     | 'S' ->
  2410. ‌      let pad = check_no_0 symb (get_padprec ()) in
  2411. ‌      let Fmt_EBB fmt_rest = parse str_ind end_ind in
  2412.       if get_ign () then
  2413. ‌        let ignored = Ignored_caml_string (get_padprec_opt '_') in
  2414.         Fmt_EBB (Ignored_param (ignored, fmt_rest))
  2415.       else
  2416. ‌        let Padding_fmt_EBB (pad', fmt_rest') =
  2417.           make_padding_fmt_ebb pad fmt_rest in
  2418.         Fmt_EBB (Caml_string (pad', fmt_rest'))
  2419.     | 'd' | 'i' | 'x' | 'X' | 'o' | 'u' ->
  2420. ‌      let iconv = compute_int_conv pct_ind str_ind (get_plus ()) (get_hash ())

  2424. ‌        let ignored = Ignored_int (iconv, get_pad_opt '_') in

  2426.       else

  2432. ‌      let counter = Token_counter in

  2436.       else

  2438.     | 'l' | 'n' | 'L' when str_ind=end_ind || not (is_int_base str.[str_ind]) ->
  2439. ‌      let Fmt_EBB fmt_rest = parse str_ind end_ind in
  2440. ‌      let counter = counter_of_char symb in
  2441.       if get_ign () then
  2442. ‌        let ignored = Ignored_scan_get_counter counter in
  2443.         Fmt_EBB (Ignored_param (ignored, fmt_rest))
  2444.       else
  2445.         Fmt_EBB (Scan_get_counter (counter, fmt_rest))
  2446.     | 'l' ->
  2447. ‌      let iconv =
  2448.         compute_int_conv pct_ind (str_ind + 1) (get_plus ()) (get_hash ())
  2449.           (get_space ()) str.[str_ind] in
  2450. ‌      let Fmt_EBB fmt_rest = parse (str_ind + 1) end_ind in
  2451.       if get_ign () then
  2452. ‌        let ignored = Ignored_int32 (iconv, get_pad_opt '_') in
  2453.         Fmt_EBB (Ignored_param (ignored, fmt_rest))
  2454.       else
  2455. ‌        let Padprec_fmt_EBB (pad', prec', fmt_rest') =
  2456.           make_padprec_fmt_ebb (get_int_pad ()) (get_prec ()) fmt_rest in
  2457.         Fmt_EBB (Int32 (iconv, pad', prec', fmt_rest'))
  2458.     | 'n' ->
  2459. ‌      let iconv =
  2460.         compute_int_conv pct_ind (str_ind + 1) (get_plus ())
  2461.           (get_hash ()) (get_space ()) str.[str_ind] in
  2462. ‌      let Fmt_EBB fmt_rest = parse (str_ind + 1) end_ind in
  2463.       if get_ign () then
  2464. ‌        let ignored = Ignored_nativeint (iconv, get_pad_opt '_') in
  2465.         Fmt_EBB (Ignored_param (ignored, fmt_rest))
  2466.       else
  2467. ‌        let Padprec_fmt_EBB (pad', prec', fmt_rest') =
  2468.           make_padprec_fmt_ebb (get_int_pad ()) (get_prec ()) fmt_rest in
  2469.         Fmt_EBB (Nativeint (iconv, pad', prec', fmt_rest'))
  2470.     | 'L' ->
  2471. ‌      let iconv =
  2472.         compute_int_conv pct_ind (str_ind + 1) (get_plus ()) (get_hash ())
  2473.           (get_space ()) str.[str_ind] in
  2474. ‌      let Fmt_EBB fmt_rest = parse (str_ind + 1) end_ind in
  2475.       if get_ign () then
  2476. ‌        let ignored = Ignored_int64 (iconv, get_pad_opt '_') in
  2477.         Fmt_EBB (Ignored_param (ignored, fmt_rest))
  2478.       else
  2479. ‌        let Padprec_fmt_EBB (pad', prec', fmt_rest') =
  2480.           make_padprec_fmt_ebb (get_int_pad ()) (get_prec ()) fmt_rest in
  2481.         Fmt_EBB (Int64 (iconv, pad', prec', fmt_rest'))
  2482.     | 'f' | 'e' | 'E' | 'g' | 'G' | 'F' | 'h' | 'H' ->
  2483. ‌      let fconv =
  2484.         compute_float_conv pct_ind str_ind
  2485.           (get_plus ()) (get_hash ()) (get_space ()) symb in
  2486. ‌      let Fmt_EBB fmt_rest = parse str_ind end_ind in
  2487.       if get_ign () then
  2488. ‌        let ignored = Ignored_float (get_pad_opt '_', get_prec_opt ()) in
  2489.         Fmt_EBB (Ignored_param (ignored, fmt_rest))
  2490.       else
  2491. ‌        let Padprec_fmt_EBB (pad', prec', fmt_rest') =
  2492.           make_padprec_fmt_ebb (get_pad ()) (get_prec ()) fmt_rest in
  2493.         Fmt_EBB (Float (fconv, pad', prec', fmt_rest'))
  2494.     | 'b' | 'B' ->
  2495. ‌      let pad = check_no_0 symb (get_padprec ()) in
  2496. ‌      let Fmt_EBB fmt_rest = parse str_ind end_ind in
  2497.       if get_ign () then
  2498. ‌        let ignored = Ignored_bool (get_padprec_opt '_') in
  2499.         Fmt_EBB (Ignored_param (ignored, fmt_rest))
  2500.       else
  2501. ‌        let Padding_fmt_EBB (pad', fmt_rest') =
  2502.           make_padding_fmt_ebb pad fmt_rest in
  2503.         Fmt_EBB (Bool (pad', fmt_rest'))
  2504.     | 'a' ->
  2505. ‌      let Fmt_EBB fmt_rest = parse str_ind end_ind in
  2506.       Fmt_EBB (Alpha fmt_rest)
  2507.     | 't' ->
  2508. ‌      let Fmt_EBB fmt_rest = parse str_ind end_ind in
  2509.       Fmt_EBB (Theta fmt_rest)
  2510.     | 'r' ->
  2511. ‌      let Fmt_EBB fmt_rest = parse str_ind end_ind in
  2512.       if get_ign () then Fmt_EBB (Ignored_param (Ignored_reader, fmt_rest))
  2513.       else Fmt_EBB (Reader fmt_rest)
  2514.     | '!' ->
  2515. ‌      let Fmt_EBB fmt_rest = parse str_ind end_ind in
  2516.       Fmt_EBB (Flush fmt_rest)
  2517.     | ('%' | '@') as c ->
  2518. ‌      let Fmt_EBB fmt_rest = parse str_ind end_ind in
  2519.       Fmt_EBB (Char_literal (c, fmt_rest))
  2520.     | '{' ->
  2521. ‌      let sub_end = search_subformat_end str_ind end_ind '}' in
  2522. ‌      let Fmt_EBB sub_fmt = parse str_ind sub_end in
  2523. ‌      let Fmt_EBB fmt_rest = parse (sub_end + 2) end_ind in
  2524. ‌      let sub_fmtty = fmtty_of_fmt sub_fmt in
  2525.       if get_ign () then
  2526. ‌        let ignored = Ignored_format_arg (get_pad_opt '_', sub_fmtty) in
  2527.         Fmt_EBB (Ignored_param (ignored, fmt_rest))
  2528.       else
  2529.         Fmt_EBB (Format_arg (get_pad_opt '{', sub_fmtty, fmt_rest))
  2530.     | '(' ->
  2531. ‌      let sub_end = search_subformat_end str_ind end_ind ')' in
  2532. ‌      let Fmt_EBB fmt_rest = parse (sub_end + 2) end_ind in
  2533. ‌      let Fmt_EBB sub_fmt = parse str_ind sub_end in
  2534. ‌      let sub_fmtty = fmtty_of_fmt sub_fmt in
  2535.       if get_ign () then
  2536. ‌        let ignored = Ignored_format_subst (get_pad_opt '_', sub_fmtty) in
  2537.         Fmt_EBB (Ignored_param (ignored, fmt_rest))
  2538.       else
  2539.         Fmt_EBB (Format_subst (get_pad_opt '(', sub_fmtty, fmt_rest))
  2540.     | '[' ->
  2541. ‌      let next_ind, char_set = parse_char_set str_ind end_ind in
  2542. ‌      let Fmt_EBB fmt_rest = parse next_ind end_ind in
  2543.       if get_ign () then
  2544. ‌        let ignored = Ignored_scan_char_set (get_pad_opt '_', char_set) in
  2545.         Fmt_EBB (Ignored_param (ignored, fmt_rest))
  2546.       else
  2547.         Fmt_EBB (Scan_char_set (get_pad_opt '[', char_set, fmt_rest))
  2548.     | '-' | '+' | '#' | ' ' | '_' ->
  2549.       failwith_message
  2550.         "invalid format %S: at character number %d, \
  2551. ‌         flag %C is only allowed after the '%%', before padding and precision"
  2552.         str pct_ind symb
  2553.     | _ ->
  2554.       failwith_message
  2555.         "invalid format %S: at character number %d, \
  2556.          invalid conversion \"%%%c\"" str (str_ind - 1) symb
  2557.     in
  2558.     (* Check for unused options, and reject them as incompatible.

  2560.        Such checks need to be disabled in legacy mode, as the legacy
  2561.        parser silently ignored incompatible flags. *)
  2562.     if not legacy_behavior then begin
  2563.     if not !plus_used && plus then
  2564.       incompatible_flag pct_ind str_ind symb "'+'";
  2565.     if not !hash_used && hash then
  2566.       incompatible_flag pct_ind str_ind symb "'#'";
  2567.     if not !space_used && space then
  2568.       incompatible_flag pct_ind str_ind symb "' '";
  2569.     if not !pad_used  && Padding_EBB pad <> Padding_EBB No_padding then
  2570.       incompatible_flag pct_ind str_ind symb "`padding'";
  2571.     if not !prec_used && Precision_EBB prec <> Precision_EBB No_precision then
  2572.       incompatible_flag pct_ind str_ind (if ign then '_' else symb)
  2573.         "`precision'";
  2574.     if ign && plus then incompatible_flag pct_ind str_ind '_' "'+'";
  2575.     end;
  2576.     (* this last test must not be disabled in legacy mode,
  2577.        as ignoring it would typically result in a different typing
  2578.        than what the legacy parser used *)
  2579.     if not !ign_used && ign then
  2580.       begin match symb with
  2581.         (* argument-less formats can safely be ignored in legacy mode *)
  2582.         | ('@' | '%' | '!' | ',') when legacy_behavior -> ()
  2583.         | _ ->
  2584.           incompatible_flag pct_ind str_ind symb "'_'"
  2585.       end;
  2586.     fmt_result

  2588.   (* Parse formatting information (after '@'). *)
  2589. ‌  and parse_after_at : type e f . int -> int -> (_, _, e, f) fmt_ebb =
  2590.   fun str_ind end_ind ->
  2591.     if str_ind = end_ind then Fmt_EBB (Char_literal ('@', End_of_format))
  2592.     else
  2593.       match str.[str_ind] with
  2594.       | '[' ->
  2595.         parse_tag false (str_ind + 1) end_ind
  2596.       | ']' ->
  2597.         let Fmt_EBB fmt_rest = parse (str_ind + 1) end_ind in
  2598.         Fmt_EBB (Formatting_lit (Close_box, fmt_rest))
  2599.       | '{' ->
  2600.         parse_tag true (str_ind + 1) end_ind
  2601.       | '}' ->
  2602. ‌        let Fmt_EBB fmt_rest = parse (str_ind + 1) end_ind in
  2603.         Fmt_EBB (Formatting_lit (Close_tag, fmt_rest))
  2604.       | ',' ->
  2605. ‌        let Fmt_EBB fmt_rest = parse (str_ind + 1) end_ind in
  2606.         Fmt_EBB (Formatting_lit (Break ("@,", 0, 0), fmt_rest))
  2607.       | ' ' ->
  2608. ‌        let Fmt_EBB fmt_rest = parse (str_ind + 1) end_ind in
  2609.         Fmt_EBB (Formatting_lit (Break ("@ ", 1, 0), fmt_rest))
  2610.       | ';' ->
  2611.         parse_good_break (str_ind + 1) end_ind
  2612.       | '?' ->

  2636.   (* Try to read the optional <name> after "@{" or "@[". *)
  2637. ‌‌  and parse_tag : type e f . bool -> int -> int -> (_, _, e, f) fmt_ebb =
  2638.   fun is_open_tag str_ind end_ind ->

  2661.   (* Try to read the optional <width offset> after "@;". *)
  2662. ‌‌  and parse_good_break : type e f . int -> int -> (_, _, e, f) fmt_ebb =
  2663.   fun str_ind end_ind ->
  2664. ‌    let next_ind, formatting_lit =

  2666.         if str_ind = end_ind || str.[str_ind] <> '<' then raise Not_found;

  2691.   (* Parse the size in a <n>. *)

  2715.   (* Parse and construct a char set. *)
  2716. ‌  and parse_char_set str_ind end_ind =
  2717.     if str_ind = end_ind then unexpected_end_of_format end_ind;

  2719.     let char_set = create_char_set () in
  2720.     let add_char c =
  2721.       add_in_char_set char_set c;
  2722.     in

  2726.       done;

  2729.     let fail_single_percent str_ind =

  2735.     (* Parse the first character of a char set. *)
  2736.     let rec parse_char_set_start str_ind end_ind =

  2741.     (* Parse the content of a char set until the first ']'. *)
  2742.     and parse_char_set_content str_ind end_ind =
  2743.       if str_ind = end_ind then unexpected_end_of_format end_ind;
  2744.       match str.[str_ind] with
  2745.       | ']' ->
  2746.         str_ind + 1
  2747.       | '-' ->
  2748.         add_char '-';
  2749.         parse_char_set_content (str_ind + 1) end_ind
  2750.       | c ->
  2751.         parse_char_set_after_char (str_ind + 1) end_ind c

  2753.     (* Test for range in char set. *)
  2754.     and parse_char_set_after_char str_ind end_ind c =
  2755.       if str_ind = end_ind then unexpected_end_of_format end_ind;
  2756.       match str.[str_ind] with

  2759.         str_ind + 1
  2760.       | '-' ->

  2762.       | ('%' | '@') as c' when c = '%' ->
  2763.         add_char c';
  2764.         parse_char_set_content (str_ind + 1) end_ind
  2765.       | c' ->
  2766.         if c = '%' then fail_single_percent str_ind;
  2767.         (* note that '@' alone is accepted, as done by the legacy
  2768.            implementation; the documentation specifically requires %@
  2769.            so we could warn on that *)
  2770.         add_char c;
  2771.         parse_char_set_after_char (str_ind + 1) end_ind c'

  2773.     (* Manage range in char set (except if the '-' the last char before ']') *)
  2774.     and parse_char_set_after_minus str_ind end_ind c =
  2775.       if str_ind = end_ind then unexpected_end_of_format end_ind;
  2776.       match str.[str_ind] with
  2777.       | ']' ->
  2778.         add_char c;
  2779.         add_char '-';
  2780.         str_ind + 1
  2781.       | '%' ->
  2782.         if str_ind + 1 = end_ind then unexpected_end_of_format end_ind;
  2783.         begin match str.[str_ind + 1] with
  2784.           | ('%' | '@') as c' ->
  2785.             add_range c c';
  2786.             parse_char_set_content (str_ind + 2) end_ind
  2787.           | _ -> fail_single_percent str_ind
  2788.         end
  2789.       | c' ->
  2790.         add_range c c';
  2791.         parse_char_set_content (str_ind + 1) end_ind
  2792.     in
  2793. ‌    let str_ind, reverse =
  2794.       if str_ind = end_ind then unexpected_end_of_format end_ind;
  2795.       match str.[str_ind] with
  2796.         | '^' -> str_ind + 1, true
  2797.         | _ -> str_ind, false in
  2798. ‌    let next_ind = parse_char_set_start str_ind end_ind in
  2799. ‌    let char_set = freeze_char_set char_set in
  2800.     next_ind, (if reverse then rev_char_set char_set else char_set)

  2802.   (* Consume all next spaces, raise an Failure if end_ind is reached. *)
  2803. ‌  and parse_spaces str_ind end_ind =
  2804.     if str_ind = end_ind then unexpected_end_of_format end_ind;
  2805.     if str.[str_ind] = ' ' then parse_spaces (str_ind + 1) end_ind else str_ind

  2807.   (* Read a positive integer from the string, raise a Failure if end_ind is
  2808.      reached. *)
  2809.   and parse_positive str_ind end_ind acc =
  2810.     if str_ind = end_ind then unexpected_end_of_format end_ind;
  2811.     match str.[str_ind] with
  2812.     | '0' .. '9' as c ->
  2813.       let new_acc = acc * 10 + (int_of_char c - int_of_char '0') in

  2816.           "invalid format %S: integer %d is greater than the limit %d"
  2817.           str new_acc Sys.max_string_length
  2818.       else
  2819.         parse_positive (str_ind + 1) end_ind new_acc
  2820.     | _ -> str_ind, acc

  2822.   (* Read a positive or negative integer from the string, raise a Failure
  2823.      if end_ind is reached. *)
  2824.   and parse_integer str_ind end_ind =
  2825.     if str_ind = end_ind then unexpected_end_of_format end_ind;
  2826.     match str.[str_ind] with
  2827.     | '0' .. '9' -> parse_positive str_ind end_ind 0
  2828.     | '-' -> (
  2829.       if str_ind + 1 = end_ind then unexpected_end_of_format end_ind;

  2831.       | '0' .. '9' ->

  2833.         next_ind, -n
  2834.       | c ->

  2837.     | _ -> assert false

  2839.   (* Add a literal to a format from a literal character sub-sequence. *)
  2840. ‌  and add_literal : type a d e f .

  2848.   (* Search the end of the current sub-format
  2849.      (i.e. the corresponding "%}" or "%)") *)
  2850. ‌  and search_subformat_end str_ind end_ind c =
  2851.     if str_ind = end_ind then
  2852.       failwith_message
  2853.         "invalid format %S: unclosed sub-format, \
  2854.          expected \"%%%c\" at character number %d" str c end_ind;
  2855.     match str.[str_ind] with
  2856.     | '%' ->
  2857.       if str_ind + 1 = end_ind then unexpected_end_of_format end_ind;
  2858.       if str.[str_ind + 1] = c then (* End of format found *) str_ind else
  2859.         begin match str.[str_ind + 1] with
  2860.         | '_' ->
  2861.           (* Search for "%_(" or "%_{". *)
  2862.           if str_ind + 2 = end_ind then unexpected_end_of_format end_ind;

  2866.             search_subformat_end (sub_end + 2) end_ind c
  2867.           | '(' ->

  2869.             search_subformat_end (sub_end + 2) end_ind c

  2871.           end
  2872.         | '{' ->
  2873.           (* %{...%} sub-format found. *)
  2874. ‌          let sub_end = search_subformat_end (str_ind + 2) end_ind '}' in
  2875.           search_subformat_end (sub_end + 2) end_ind c
  2876.         | '(' ->

  2883.         | ')' ->

  2885.           expected_character (str_ind + 1) "character '}'" ')'

  2889.     | _ -> search_subformat_end (str_ind + 1) end_ind c

  2891.   (* Check if symb is a valid int conversion after "%l", "%n" or "%L" *)

  2901.   (* Convert (plus, symb) to its associated int_conv. *)

  2905.     | false, false,  true, 'd' -> Int_sd | false, false,  true, 'i' -> Int_si

  2908.     | false,  true, false, 'x' -> Int_Cx | false,  true, false, 'X' -> Int_CX
  2909.     | false, false, false, 'o' -> Int_o

  2911.     | false, false, false, 'u' -> Int_u

  2925.         compute_int_conv pct_ind str_ind plus hash false symb
  2926.       else incompatible_flag pct_ind str_ind ' ' "'+'"
  2927.     | false, _, true, _    ->
  2928.       if legacy_behavior then (* ignore *)
  2929.         compute_int_conv pct_ind str_ind plus hash false symb
  2930.       else incompatible_flag pct_ind str_ind symb "' '"
  2931.     | true, _, false, _    ->
  2932.       if legacy_behavior then (* ignore *)

  2935.     | false, _, false, _ -> assert false

  2937.   (* Convert (plus, space, symb) to its associated float_conv. *)
  2938.   and compute_float_conv pct_ind str_ind plus hash space symb =

  2942.     |  true, false -> Float_flag_p
  2943.     |  true,  true ->
  2944.       (* plus and space: legacy implementation prefers plus *)

  2946.       else incompatible_flag pct_ind str_ind ' ' "'+'" in
  2947.     let kind = match hash, symb with
  2948.     | _, 'f' -> Float_f
  2949.     | _, 'e' -> Float_e
  2950.     | _, 'E' -> Float_E
  2951.     | _, 'g' -> Float_g
  2952.     | _, 'G' -> Float_G
  2953.     | _, 'h' -> Float_h
  2954.     | _, 'H' -> Float_H
  2955.     | false, 'F' -> Float_F
  2956.     | true, 'F' -> Float_CF
  2957.     | _ -> assert false in
  2958.     flag, kind

  2960.   (* Raise [Failure] with a friendly error message about incompatible options.*)
